events.name: Getting Started with Essential Oils - Coogee
events.summary: Heard about essential oils? Maybe you already use them? Maybe you have always wanted to find out more? What if I said there was a way to liv
events.description_html:
Heard about essential oils? Maybe you already use them? Maybe you have always wanted to find out more? What if I said there was a way to live a more natural and healthier life? Would you want to find out more?

Essential oils can enhance so many areas of your daily life. They're often used for immune support, relaxation and sleep, stress relief, emotional balance, skin care, respiratory health, cleaning, and even muscle tension and pain.

Here's your opportiunity to find out more. We are going to give you all the tools to help get started with essential oils.

You will learn about essential oil safety, how essential oils are produced, and common methods of use. You'll also learn how to create a more natural, healthy lifestyle through the use of essential oils.

Some of the topics we will be covering on the day include:

  • What essential oils are?

  • How they work

  • How they are produced

  • Managing stress with essential oils

  • Natural remedies for everyday ailments and sniffles

  • Dealing with sleep problems the natural way

You will have opportunities to experience essential oils first hand and understand the best way to source oils for you and your family.

If you have any questions, please contact us at hello@welloiledmachine.co.uk.

We look forward to meeting you.

events.summary: Yoga invites you to move consciously while connecting to your breathe. It helps to slow our minds down, bring awareness inwards and facilita
events.description_html:
Yoga invites you to move consciously while connecting to your breathe. It helps to slow our minds down, bring awareness inwards and facilitates the stillness required for meditation. Classes are open to all, regardless of finance, experience, age, shape, size and ability.

Classes led by certified yoga teachers Kate Sherman, Mariam Nakhla, Betsy Lea from Revel in Motion Yoga and Amelie Patrux from Feel-in(g) Slow Yoga.

EVERY SUNDAY @ 8.30 AM (Please arrive at least 5 minutes before the class as we start teaching at 8.30 sharp and you might interfere with other students who arrived on time).
All Welcome | By Donation (as much or as little as you can).

Experience Level: 
All - For all levels of experience

This class is BY DONATION - Our community at the Sydney Buddhist Centre is based on 'dana', the Sanskrit term for generosity – people giving their time and energy to create something together. We aim to offer our activities open-handedly. Please feel free to contribute as much or as little as you can after each class. There is a donation bowl available. Our teachers come on a voluntary basis.

FAQs

Do I have to bring my own yoga mat?

No, we provide all yoga props for this class including mats. They are second-hand but kept clean by cleaning them regularly. Feel free to bring your own if you wish or bring a towel to cover the mat.

What are my transport/parking options for getting to and from the event?

On Enmore Road, you can find 2-hour parking spots for free (don't forget to print the parking ticket). You can also go down the little streets around to find 2-hour free parking. If you are coming by public transport, the Newtown Train Station is a 2-min walk.

Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?

No, just give your name on arrival.

events.name: Family Day Care Childcare Information Sessions 2020
events.summary:
Join us at a Family Day Care Childcare Information Session to learn about this wonderful childcare option for families.
You'll hear from a p
events.description_html:
Join us at a Family Day Care Childcare Information Session to learn about this wonderful childcare option for families.

You'll hear from a parent about their family's experience with Family Day Care, discover how Family Day Care works, learn about its benefits for young children and meet our experienced Educators.

Sutherland Shire Council's Family Day Care service features 24 early childhood specialists who work out of their own homes, providing care and education to small groups of young children.

Our Family Day Care team provides warm and nurturing environments, maintains close connections and communication with families and prepares their daily program specifically for the needs and milestones of each child.

More than 200 children enjoy the benefits of our Family Day Care service. Families tell us what they value most is consistency – they arrive at care and are greeted by one Educator who knows their child well.

Families receive detailed information about their child’s day – the activities they engaged in, their learning areas of focus and how their child is building their strengths. It’s a level of communication unique to Family Day Care.

A parent recently said their Family Day Care Educator "has been an amazing part of my child's life. The environment, play equipment, educational program and level of care is just outstanding. I'm not sure as a parent I could've done better for him. We are so happy we found our Educator and she is able to care for my son in such an incredible way."

FAQs

What is the format of the Information Session?

Please arrive at the 9.30am start time, to ensure you don't miss out on our two wonderful speakers - a brief overview of our Family Day Care program from Council and a parent who will share their family & child's experience in Family Day Care.

What parking is available?

Street parking is available. You may wish to use the Council car park at the front of the main Council building however please note it is timed parking on Saturday mornings. Merton Street and Stapleton Avenue, at the back of the Council building, also have street parking. 

Can I bring my child/children to the event?

Children are welcome to attend this event in the company of their parents/guardians. There is limited space for prams in a quiet room inside the venue.

How can I contact the organiser with any questions?

Please call Caren Dunn ph 9710 0604 or drop us an email cjdunn@ssc.nsw.gov.au and we'll get right back to you.

Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?

Printed tickets are not required.

events.name: Edge Business Networking Breakfast
events.summary: By attending our business networking breakfasts you will have an opportunity to meet and network with group members who have a very high cal
events.description_html:
By attending our business networking breakfasts you will have an opportunity to meet and network with group members who have a very high calibre of contacts and potential referral partners for you.

 A sample of some of the people you will meet includes:-

  • A branding director whose current / past clients include NSW Health, Westpac, NSW Treasury and more;
  • A business advisor who is a Start Up Australia ambassador and has a very high level of success in building, growing and selling businesses - both his own and other people's.
  • An IT specialist who performed global IT support for Virgin management senior execs on Richard Branson’s boat as well as assisting with IT for Kylie Kwong and Luke Mangan.
  • A bookkeeping agency Director whose current and past clients include Rachel Ruddick, One Teaspoon, FBI Fashion College, MaxMara, Matt Church and Fast Ed
  • An executive coach with contacts at BMW, Fox Sports, Ernst & Young and UTS
  • A natural health and fertility expert whose clients include ‘hatted’ chefs and well known actors

 and many others with amazing networks and contacts that they can introduce you to.

 

Please book in quickly as we only have a limited number of visitor spots available and they will go fast.

BNI - Business Network International is a business and professional networking organization whose primary purpose is to exchange qualified business referrals. It is the largest networking organisation of its kind. Currently, BNI has over 6400 chapters internationally. Last year, members of BNI passed 7 million referrals, which generated $3.2 Billion worth of business for each other.

 What makes BNI unique is that it allows only one person per classification to join a chapter.  Thus, once you have joined, none of your competitors can participate.

Remember to bring plenty of business cards to pass around, as you will meet lots of local business professionals.

events.name: MDCTP Intellectual Property Workshop [WEBINAR]
events.summary:
MDCTP Intellectual Property Workshop [WEBINAR]
While COVID-19 presents us with many challenges, we also recognise the opportunities: in the
events.description_html:
MDCTP Intellectual Property Workshop [WEBINAR]

While COVID-19 presents us with many challenges, we also recognise the opportunities: in the spirit of sharing, and for the first time in the 6 year history of the NSW Medical Device Commercialisation Training Program (MDCTP), NSW Health and Cicada Innovations will open the Intellectual Property Workshop to participants outside of NSW - and it's free to participate! At a time when we will be looking to our brightest minds more than ever to solve new and pressing problems, we want to do everything we can to support the continued growth and learning of Australia's innovators. 

MDCTP IP is a one-day workshop delivered together with Australia’s leading intellectual property firm, Davies Collison Cave, that focuses on intellectual property management strategies for medical devices. It is designed to equip candidates with the necessary knowledge to protect their intellectual property through trademarks, patents and design registration. Candidates will learn about the different types of intellectual property, protection strategies and how to speak about their medical research or technology without giving away their secret sauce.

This workshop is FREE to participants but you MUST register! Do it today! We look forward to meeting you on the 28th of April!

events.name: 2020 NHMRC Postgraduate Scholarship Workshop
events.summary: The NHMRC Postgraduate Scholarships scheme funds successful applicants to attain a research based postgraduate degree (Doctor of Philosophy
events.description_html:
The NHMRC Postgraduate Scholarships scheme funds successful applicants to attain a research based postgraduate degree (Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) or a Master’s).  It aims to support outstanding health and medical graduates early in their career, so they can be trained to conduct research that is internationally competitive and to develop a capacity for original independent research within Australia.

The workshop will cover all aspects including strategic advice, compliance issues and feedback from supervisors experienced with this scheme. The workshop will be open to applicants and their supervisors. Please register here for workshop.

In preparation of this workshop, please familiarise yourself with the specific rules regarding this scheme, prepare a draft application and prepare questions that would like to discuss. It is important that you have your draft prepared at this stage as the internal application deadline is on 13th May 2020.

Please register by Friday, 24 April 2020.

Thank you and we looking forward to meeting you.

events.summary: COVID-19 coronavirus update: Please be advised that our 2020 training events will still be held live however they will be delivered online v
events.description_html:
COVID-19 coronavirus update: Please be advised that our 2020 training events will still be held live however they will be delivered online via live stream from our office in Potts Point (Sydney) NSW Australia.


"We have learned so much and got an abundance of valuable information from the work shop. Value for money was absolutely there for us. We are so happy that we made this decision, the insight into the property development industry from your knowledge and experience was an eye opener. Thank you for sharing so many of your contacts with us and offering your ongoing support, this will definitely help us. We are now much more confident going forward into bigger projects on our own." Joseph B.

"Having done multiple property development training courses I can say he is a world class educator with a tonne of experience" Peter A

Steve Chandler, a third generation property developer with 39 years' experience in the industry, takes you on a journey deep diving into all things property development from how to approach home owners for acquiring their property for your project, through demonstrating how to undertake feasibility studies, preparing and obtaining development approvals, identifying niche markets to maximise revenues and how to deliver the building with minimum defects.

The course is based upon the 5 fundamentals of property development:

  1. Acquisition;
  2. Feasibility;
  3. Authorities;
  4. Revenue; and
  5. Delivery.

Over 3 days there are no PowerPoint presentations whatsoever, only genuine property development activities using real property development techniques and tools. 

Feel free to contact us on +61 2 9357 1003 to discuss the course and its content.

 

FAQs

 

What are my transport/parking options for getting to and from the event?

Public transport is avaiable in close proximity to the venue.

 

What can I bring into the event?

Please bring your laptop or tablet for participation in activities throughout the course.

We highly recommend bringing a jumper or jacket as the room can become cold during the event when sitting for long periods of time.

 

How can I contact the organiser with any questions?

Please contact us at email developer@propertydevelopmentinstitute.com or phone our office on +61 2 9357 1003.

 

Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?

You do not have to bring your printed ticket to the event as we will have a list of attendees.

 

Can I update my registration information?

You may update your registration information at any time by contaccting us.

 

Is my registration fee or ticket transferrable?

Your registration/ticket is fully transferrable however please ensure that the recipient of your ticket is aware of our terms and conditons of sale. You will also need to contact us prior to the event to advise us of the change otherwise we will assume your ticket has been stolen by the person in attendance.

Thanks for your interest in UNSW Founders, Australia’s most comprehensive university entrepreneurship program. Our coaching services and pre-accelerator and accelerator programs are free and accessible to UNSW students, academic staff and Alumni – for life!

These information sessions run online from 12-1pm. You will be emailed the zoom meeting link 24 hours prior to the session (please check your junk folder if you have not received).

Please download the zoom software prior to the meeting time: https://unsw.zoom.us/

This is a great opportunity for you to connect with our startup coaches, fellow entrepreneurs and kick off your journey with UNSW Founders. 

Agenda:

1. Completing the UNSW Founders intake form

2. Who’s in the virtual room

3. UNSW Founders programs and services

4. Matching you with a coach

5. Q&A

Unfortunately, some elements of the UNSW Founders programs and services are not available to professional staff, unless you are also UNSW alumni.

Terms and Conditions apply.

PRIVACY STATEMENT

UNSW is collecting your personal information in this form for the purpose of providing you with more information about the UNSW Founders Program. UNSW is using a third party (Microsoft) to provide the technology platform for this registration form on behalf of UNSW. As a result, any personal information you provide in this form will be processed by Microsoft. Information collected by the University through this form may be processed outside of New South Wales and Australia. The supply of personal information is voluntary. You can request access to and amendment of information we hold about you by contacting founders@unsw.edu.au. The privacy and confidentiality of the personal information held about you will be respected. Personal information collected by UNSW is managed in accordance with its Privacy Management Plan.

By registering for this event/workshop you grant UNSW Founders full rights to use the images from any photography/video footage for publicity and education purposes. This may include (but is not limited to), the right to use them in their printed and online publicity, coursework presentations, social media and press releases. Australian Central Standard Time: 1100hrs - 1500hrs

Many influences change the value of commercial property, some inside and some outside of your control. So, what influences can help maximise your properties’ performance?


Join the Valuation for Non-Valuers online live class to discover easy-to-understand valuation principles with an added fund management perspective.



It’s relevant for all non-valuers in the property industry, and covers:

  • Main drivers affecting value
  • Main valuation methods
  • Importance of cashflow timing
  • Maximising income
  • Capitalisation Method
  • How your decisions affect value
  • Strategies to maximise property performance
  • Challenging your valuer’s assumptions



Presented by Richard Dunham Stacey, an experienced fund manager and trainer.  This online live class is interactive, engaging and insightful.

events.name: Introduction to Modern Cloth Nappies
events.summary: Disposable nappies were created as parents increasingly wanted freedom from washing nappies. A former assistant beauty editor of America Vog
events.description_html:
Disposable nappies were created as parents increasingly wanted freedom from washing nappies. A former assistant beauty editor of America Vogue, Marion Donovan came from a family of inventors. She began creating plastic coverings for cloth nappies to stop leakage, using shower curtain material. In 1946 she patented "the boater" made from parachute cloth. It covered the cloth nappy. It was successfully marketed from 1949.

Procter and Gamble were the first company to make serious money out of the nappy with their own design that came later when they launched Pampers in the USA in 1961. The first pamper still lies in landfill with full biodegradability estimated at 150 years. The first disposable nappy was sold in Australia in 1965. Over 400 billion (an incomprehensible amount) of disposable nappies remain in landfills throughout the world.

Would you like to reduce waste and stop the use of disposable nappies?

We are conducting a free information session on modern cloth nappies. This workshop will show you how easy the modern cloth nappy is to use and clean, and will help you decide which style of nappy will suit your baby best.

 The modern cloth nappy is vastly different from cloth nappies of the past. They are very user friendly, come in a range of sizes, colours, patterns and fabric types with no safety pins in sight!

This session will cover the following information.

  • The benefits of using cloth nappies.
  • The different styles of cloth nappies available.
  • What you need to start using cloth nappies.
  • How to fit the nappies and care for them.
  • What all is involved in cleaning the cloth nappies.
  • Discuss the economic and environmental benefits of cloth nappies.

 The workshop also includes a hands-on component with baby dolls to try them out on. The all-important question of "What do I do with the poo?" will also be answered!

Current cloth nappy users can bring along any cloth nappies you have if you'd like help with fitting or support using them.

 Workshop facilitator, Alice, has been using modern cloth nappies on her young children from when they were born, and has run many nappy workshop across Sydney and the Illawarra.

 New and expecting parents, grandparents, and carers are all welcome.

 

FAQs

 

What are my transport/parking options for getting to and from the event?

Workshop participants to make their own way to 673 Anzac Parade Maroubra (Maroubra Library). 

 What can I bring into the event?

Participants to bring their own water bottle as all Council events are free of single use plastics.

 How can I contact the organiser with any questions?

You can contact the workshop organiser by email: anil.gupta@randwick.nsw.gov.au

 Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?

No. Council encourages reduction of waste and hence will have the names of the participants from the booking form.

Become a Better Business Leader and Make Better Decisions By Knowing Your Numbers

 

Now, more than ever, it is vital to understand your business numbers so that you can make better, more informed decisions. This will give your business the best chance of maintaining profitability and emerging from this Coronavirus crisis in the best shape possible, and allow you to take advantage of the opportunities when things turn around later.

 

In this 90 minute webinar, we will cover the following areas:

 

  • Profit & Loss Statements and Balance Sheets Made Simple

  • KPIs and the Importance of Tracking the Key Numbers

  • Understanding Your Break-Even Point 

  • Setting Revenue Targets and Activity Targets for Your Team

  • Learn the Fundamentals of Good Cashflow Management

  • Understand the Power of Pricing (and the Danger of Discounting)

 

He will teach you the fundamentals of business financials and the key numbers that you should be tracking in your business. You will leave with the confidence to look at your numbers with a new sense of understanding and clarity and this will lead you to become a more capable and successful business owner or manager.

Our Financial Capability Coaching Training offers a range of practical coaching tools for Community Sector Workers to:

  • Support your own money wellness
  • Be confident about having meaningful and productive money conversations with the people and communities you work with

This training has been developed and trialled by Good Shepherd Australia New Zealand over two years. It is based on our research and evidence-based outcomes in supporting women to create and sustain a productive relationship with money. It is supported by our approach and findings in our Firmer Foundations® program.

Financial Capability Coaching

We define financial capability coaching as: “…a process by which people determine their financial goals and the pathways and tools they need to achieve these goals. Coaching recognises that people are experts on themselves, their lives and the outcomes they are seeking. Through the coaching process, people maintain ownership of their goals to create sustainable change and greater self-determination.”


Training background and rationale

This training provides both personal and professional development.

  • Personal development: the course will support you to understand your own relationship with money and how to set and reach financial goals as an essential building block to money wellness
  • Professional development: People who participate in our services commonly face financial challenges: in particular, women who have experienced economic abuse or family violence. This course will provide you with confidence and skills to hold strengths-based money conversations with women as a way of increasing their money wellness and confidence, and decreasing their vulnerability to economic abuse or family violence.


Training delivery

Training is delivered through two interactive modules, over 2.5 days. Participants can elect to do Module One only if they wish. Both modules are recommended for people working intensively with women and their families who are experiencing financial stress and disadvantage.


Cost: The program is completely free

Registration is essential

If you have any questions, please call Emily Ninnes
on 02 8571 7800 or email emily.ninnes@goodshep.org.au


Module One (1 day) – My Money Wellness

See Eventbrite for details of dates and venues

This module will equip participants to have simple financial capability coaching conversations with clients, using a strengths-based approach that is collaborative and respectful of people’s personal experience.
At the end of My Money Wellness, participants will be able to:

  • Tell their own money story and understand the money stories of others
  • Identify the signs of economic abuse
  • Understand the foundational concepts of financial capability coaching and how to apply them to their life and work, including what it feels like to be “coached”
  • Use simple coaching tools with confidence
  • Have simple financial coaching conversations


Module Two (1.5 days) – Financial Capability Coaching Conversations

See Eventbrite for details of dates and venues

Day One: 9:30 am – 4.30 pm

Day Two: 9:30am – 2.00 pm

This training builds on the material in Module One: My Money Wellness with a focus on practice and technique. On completing Financial Capability Coaching Conversations participants will be able to:

  • Better understand the money stories of others, including the effect of economic abuse, trauma, intergenerational poverty and family violence on a person’s money story
  • Understand how our own money stories can influence the money conversations we have
  • with others
  • Understand and confidently use financial capability coaching tools, techniques and practice, including what it feels like to “coach”
  • Have productive and meaningful financial coaching conversations

events.name: VERSCHOBEN  auf 29.8.2020 - Burg & Stadt HARDEGG & Wildkatzen im NP Thayatal
events.description_html:
Ersatztermin wurde angelegt: https://www.meetup.com/de-DE/Wien-erleben/events/269619962/

VERSCHOBEN

Nach langem Nachdenken und Nachspüren, bin ich mit dem Waldviertler Tourismusbüro und dem Busunternehmen überein gekommen, dass wir nicht bis zum Schluß abwarten ob und wie lange alle Freizeitbetriebe geschlossen werden bleiben müssen. Bis nach Ostern sowieso und wir denken es wird noch länger dauern.
Daher habe ich unseren Busausflug auf Samstag, den 29. August 2020 verschoben.
ACHTUNG: Es kann keine Rückzahlung deines Kostenbeitrages erfolgen. Er bleibt für diesen Tag gültig.
Falls du am[masked] nicht teilnehmen kannst, musst du dir selber Ersatz suchen! Ersatzperson bitte bei mir mittels PN melden.
BITTE ES MELDET SICH HIER NIEMAND AB, damit ich die Übersicht behalten kannt.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"BURG & STADT HARDEGG mit Wildkatzenfütterung im Nationalpark Thayatal"

Wir fahren traditionell wieder mit dem Busunternehmen „Mitterbauer“.

Ich bitte um Verständnis, dass die ersten zwei Reihen für Meetuper/innen mit Reisekrankheit oder anderen körperlichen Beeinträchtigungen reserviert sind.

Bitte mich per PN SOFORT bei Anmeldung verständigen, wer so einen Platz benötigt!

Ansonsten ist freie Platzwahl!

-------------------------

"PROGRAMM:"

siehe neues Treffen: https://www.meetup.com/de-DE/Wien-erleben/events/269619962/

------------------------

Majestätisch auf einem Felsen über der kleinsten Stadt Österreichs thront die Burg Hardegg. Mit 600 Metern Umfang ist die Burg einer der größten Wehranlangen Niederösterreichs. Bei einem Rundgang durch die historischen Räumlichkeiten erleben wir die Geschichte des Gebäudes hautnah und erfahren in einer umfangreichen Ausstellung weitere spannende Details rund um die Burg Hardegg, die Familie Khevenhüller-Metsch und den Bruder von Kaiser Franz Joseph I. – Kaiser Maximilian I.

-------------------------

Wildkatzenfütterung

Sie galt als ausgestorben in Österreich und ist wieder da! Die Wildkatze – ein scheuer, unauffälliger und dennoch faszinierender Waldbewohner – hat sich wieder in Österreich in den Wäldern rund um den Nationalpark Thayatal angesiedelt. Seit Jahrzehnten galt die Wildkatze in Österreich als ausgestorben, doch Proben beweisen: Sie ist zurückgekehrt!
Wildkatzen mit eigenen Augen erleben
Obwohl es nahezu unmöglich ist, sie in freier Wildbahn zu sehen, bietet der Nationalpark Thayatal eine einmalige Chance, diese extrem scheuen Tiere zu erblicken. In Österreichs größter Wildkatzenanlage beim Nationalparkhaus Thayatal können Sie die Wildkatzen bei der Nahrungssuche, beim Herumklettern oder einfach nur beim Faulenzen beobachten. Absolutes Highlight sind die Schaufütterungen, bei denen auch die Wildheit dieser eleganten Tiere zum Vorschein kommt.

------------------------------

"PREIS PRO PERSON:"

€ 64,-

Im Preis enthalten – pro Person gerechnet und aufgeschlüsselt:

Busfahrt (€ 24,50), Paket: Eintritt und Führung Burg und Stadt Hardegg, drei-gängiges Mittagessen (ohne Getränke), Eintritt und Schaufütterung Nationalpark Thayatal (€ 37,-), Trinkgeld für Busfahrer (€ 1,-), Trinkgelder für drei Führungen (insgesamt € 1,50)

ACHTUNG: Gruppenpreise schalten immer automatisch JEDE Ermäßigungskarte (wie z.B. NÖ-CARD, WIEN-CARD etc.) aus.

---------------

events.description_html:
Au programme
Une journée partagée de théâtre en conscience, dans la nature et la bienveillance.
Apprendre à jouer et à "ne pas jouer"... Faire du moment scénique un moment d'authenticité, de présence et de vérité, pour un "je" vivant, juste et défait de ses masques sociaux...donc un "je" touchant. Entrer sur scène pour incarner un humain, un être "entier", avec ses forces et ses failles.

On croit "faire du théâtre" et on s'aperçoit que c'est le théâtre qui nous fait ; Et nous défait.

À prendre avec vous
De quoi partager pour le repas tous ensemble !

Important
Toutes les infos sur les stages du samedi sur www.lagrangeauxloups.org
Mélanie :[masked]

events.name: ONLINE : UNDERSTANDING PAINTINGS -  Study Day
events.description_html:
Confused about art? Uncertain what to look for? Want to make your gallery visits more enjoyable? Your dinner conversation more scintillating?

A quick-fix study day to help you get on top of the main aspects of looking at and understanding pantings.

10.30 -11.30 am: What Is It Made Of? A potted history of techniques . Learn to identify a painting made in fresco, tempera and oil.

11.30- 12.00 coffee break

12.00- 13.15: Know Your Styles. Quick overview to help you identify main features of the art of the Middle Ages, Renaissance, Baroque, Rococo and modern periods

13.15 - 14.00 lunch break

14.00 - 15.15 Reading a Painting: a look at Attributes, Symbols, Emblems and Allegories.

[masked] until 10.30 am

The cost of the study day is £15 per person.
To ensure your place it’s essential to make a payment in advance to

Ms L Bauman

events.name: ONLINE Creative Acquisition Workshop
events.organiser: FLIP Houses with Real Investor in RIVERSIDE
events.description_html:
This is a live streaming event. You have to have zoom acc to participate in this event.
This Workshop will cost you $20.

You will be inspired by these creative techniques and strategies for acquiring and gaining control of investment properties. Basic investment skills, terminology, and understanding of potential seller motivations will provide a solid foundation for purchasing properties once they are found.

- Learn insider tips to working with sellers in pre-foreclosure and those who are nearing an auction date
- How to gain access to potential investment properties before they hit the market
- Learn how to position yourself as an investor resource that may help them solve some of their challenges
- Compare the benefits of getting funded through institutional banks versus private lenders and how to create and maintain active property lists
- Learn creative acquisition strategies on off-market properties

Speaker: Gavin McCaleb

Gavin McCaleb is a real estate investor, trainer, and licensed broker in Idaho. With over 13 years of experience, Gavin has participated in hundreds of transactions, including single-family, multi-family, and commercial. He has developed and taught real estate courses on many subjects ranging from Short Sales, Foreclosures, Tax Sales, Property Management, Lease Options, and Subject To.

events.name: [Webinar] Real Estate Town Hall IV - Q&A on the Impact of Coronavirus
events.description_html:
💻 Online Webinar | 📆 Saturday, April 25th | 10 AM Pacific

SIGN UP HERE 👉 https://go.MultifamilyU.com/02-Town-Hall-IV

Join us for our new Impact of Coronavirus Real Estate Town Hall, a freewheeling, entertaining discussion about the extraordinary events unfolding today. In demand Real Estate presenters Neal Bawa, Anna Myers, Victor Menasce and Omar Khan will answer your questions about the Pandemic and its impact on Multifamily Syndications and as many other topics as we can cram into an hour.

This is a zero-PowerPoint live discussion and listed below are just some of the questions we will answer. Join hundreds of concerned real estate investors for a frank and brutally honest discussion on what this black swan event means for your assets, life and real estate prospects.

GET ANSWERS TO THESE QUESTIONS AND MORE…

✅ How has lending changed?

✅ Is it time to swoop in for bargains?

✅ How is the state of the debt market?

✅ Do you think the market will return to normal soon?

✅ How to value assets going forward?

✅ Should investors hold off on new investments?

✅ How has the multifamily acquisition transaction cycle changed?

✅ What types of opportunistic investing options do you expect to see?

✅ What should good asset managers be doing right now?

✅ How are distributions from multifamily syndications likely to be impacted?

✅ Demand/supply fundamentals and their impact by market and product type (Class A, B and C)

✅ Which asset classes do you expect to thrive in the post-Covid-19 environment?

✅ How are you doing with occupancy and rent collection? How are you handling the downturn?

✅ Are construction projects being impacted? If so, how?

✅ What is the impact of all the helicopter money (Fed printing money) on the economy?

✅ Should multifamily syndication investors be worried about losing their investment?

WHAT IF I CAN’T ATTEND THE LIVE TOWN HALL?

You don’t have to be present for the live webinar. Register and watch the replay video at your convenience.

SIGN UP HERE 👉 https://go.MultifamilyU.com/02-Town-Hall-IV

events.name: "Real Estate Investing: Making it Work for You" 2020 Conference & Expo
events.organiser: Real Estate Secured Note Investors - An AZREIA Sub Group
events.description_html:
Alan Langston, Arizona Real Estate Investors Association’s Executive Director, stood on stage at AZREIA’s January membership meeting in Phoenix and described what has become one of the longest real estate cycles in United States history. He added that what may have worked for you in the past might not work moving forward.

AZREIA’s “Real Estate Investing: Making It Work for You!” Conferences & Expos have consisted of multiple education tracks, along with product and service providers to assist small business real estate investors in navigating business and market trends. This year, AZREIA returns with three tracks of learning:

• Core Skills Track: For those who are new or just beginning their journey into real estate investing, AZREIA has identified the “Core Skills” every real estate and rental property investor needs which include: comping and estimating properties and repairs, leveraging marketing for lead generation, and the art of negotiations.

• Investing Solutions Track: Running a small business, regardless of the industry, the two most precious resources are money…AND TIME! We are gathering local industry subject matter experts to discuss industry trends that affect the way business is done, which will give you more of the things you want back in your real estate business.

• Alternative Investing Track: As discussed in the “Blue Ocean Strategy,” opportunity exists where others aren’t looking or working. AZREIA explores the alternative investment strategies that have begun to emerge with the population and demographic changes that are happening in the Phoenix/Arizona landscape. This track is designed to help any investor diversify their portfolio and create their own “blue ocean.”

AZREIA is also partnering with the Home Depot to create the “Home Depot Pavilion,” an experiential learning opportunity that focuses on critical areas of the home to showcase rehabbing trends in the kitchen and bathroom, and value adds to your next real estate project.

Through the “Real Estate Investing: Making It Work for You!” 2020 Conference & Expo, we are poised to bring together subject matter experts from Phoenix, Arizona and beyond to begin the conversation of where opportunities exist and what the 21st century real estate investor looks like. We are at a critical point as an industry to bring our community together to have a conversation around how real estate entrepreneurs can continue to leverage our ability to be Arizona housing providers and discuss what our part in the ongoing housing shortage looks like.

events.organiser: Ann Arbor Real Estate Investors Club
events.description_html:
Imagine meeting and enjoying coffee with like minded, smart fellow investors at your favorite Cafe. That's what I'm trying to create here.

Grab a cup of coffee (or your favorite alternate beverage), and lets have a discussion with some of the best, brightest, and most giving folks in the real estate investing world. This is a new world approach to an old (but good idea). The idea is for the more experienced members of the group to discuss, answer questions, and otherwise just HELP those with less experience. It's a simple concept really.
Many years ago, we used to meet at Nick's Pancake House on Saturday mornings, but we quickly outgrew the available space. The food and service were great, but the acoustics, logistics of order taking/ delivery, and the inevitable side conversations made these unproductive.
Enter 2020, COVID-19, and Zoom, and we have an awesome new opportunity. Not only are we able to avoid the aforementioned issues, but we have the added benefit of having investors able to join us from not just the immediate geographic area, but from ANYWHERE. This opens up amazing opportunities for the group that I hadn't really thought about a month ago.
Anyway, my go forward plan is to continue to host Classes, Guest Speaker Events, Focused Mastermind Groups, a Rainmaker Group, and now, an ONLINE Cafe, which is a great NETWORKING and LEARNING Opportunity in a casual setting. We're also now getting much more active on Facebook with an A2REIC Page, and a Private VIP Member Group to which you're all invited.
None of us are as smart as all of us, and as iron sharpens iron, one sharpens another.
We have an incredibly awesome group of members, willing to share, give, and help each other not only survive, but ultimately thrive.
I hope you'll join us. I believe you need to RSVP to get the Zoom link.
I'll make it well worth your time. We'll finish early this week, so you can get on with your day.
In the meantime, I hope you and your families are staying safe, and I look forward to a great session.

The Prince of Peace Food Pantry Distribution this Saturday, April 25th is deemed essential by Orange County and the City of Orlando and will happen.

Those who walk up to the distribution will also practice social distancing.

We will need additional volunteers for this distribution. All volunteers must be healthy, without preexisting conditions or risk factors which would make them susceptible to the coronavirus.

Volunteer roles include taking bags of food to a guest's car, helping direct traffic in and out of our campus, and taking required information from guests upon arrival.

If you are able to help, please RSVP through the Sign Up Genius link and sign up for a position. Please arrive by 7:30 so that instructions can be provided our doors open.

Closed toe shoes are required as well as any red shirt to designate you as a volunteer. We promise that you will have a rewarding morning filled with putting food into the hands of those in need.

events.name: Volunteer Opportunity: City Harvest Mobile Market: Hamilton Heights
events.description_html:
PLEASE READ - This Healthy Neighborhoods Mobile Market volunteer effort will start at 8am, a bit earlier than normally due to the current Coronavirus health issue. Although the meetup is planned to end by 12pm, it may end earlier due to participant attendance. Please RSVP through the meetup group, as well as register through the City Harvest website at the link below (if you haven't already). Thanks!

https://cityharvestvolunteers.civicore.com/index.php?section=indGpRegistrations&action=profile_conditional&fwID=8863

The Registration process is as follows:

• Follow the Group Sign-up Link above and click "New User" to create a new volunteer profile and click "Submit" (if you previously registered on the City Harvest website before, simply log in with the information from your previous registration).

• Read project details and click "Register" to confirm participation

• You will then receive a confirmation email and a reminder the day before the project

Only 10 volunteers are needed. All volunteers must be 18 years and older.

Description of Duties:

All food is distributed free of charge and the volunteer effort WILL BE indoors in the event of bad weather.

Volunteers will be stationed at 3-4 market tables, each supplied with thousands of pounds of fresh produce that they will help distribute to eligible market-goers. Sample produce items may include bananas, onions, cabbage, or potatoes - the food offered can vary from month to month, depending on what City Harvest has available. As the market-goers stop by each table, volunteers greet them-and then weigh and bag the produce, then distribute.

That's it for now. If you have any questions, feel free to give me (Daniel) a call or text at[masked]. Thanks!

About City Harvest Healthy Neighborhoods Program

Nearly 1.4 million New Yorkers are facing hunger and for many people that City Harvest serves, healthy food is unavailable and unaffordable. In turn, diseases related to poor nutrition – including diabetes and heart disease – tend to be concentrated where demand for emergency food is greatest.

As a natural extension of the anti-hunger work we began more than 30 years ago, City Harvest developed Healthy Neighborhoods programs to respond to the need for emergency food, improve access to fruits and vegetables for residents in low-income communities and provide nutrition education that will inspire affordable, healthy meal choices. Through our Healthy Neighborhoods programs, City Harvest partners with residents, community organizations, after school programs, and local businesses. Together we work to achieve a long-term impact in the fight against hunger by engaging residents in healthy choices and enhancing the local food landscape. Building off our nutrition education classes which began in 2000, and our Mobile Markets which began in 2004, City Harvest has since expanded Healthy Neighborhoods programs to high-need communities across the five boroughs.

events.organiser: Random Acts of Kindness Volunteer / Non-Profit Meetup
events.description_html:
PLEASE READ THIS ENTIRE SECTION TO SEE HOW THIS WORKS:

*** What is TangoTab? ***
TangoTab isn’t a sandwich event, but we love bringing people together to make an impact in their own community. We do that through our Feed The City events, but through TangoTab you can make an even bigger impact and it won’t cost you a cent. TangoTab is a mobile app that you use to find and check-in at restaurants. Every time you check-in at a restaurant on the app, TangoTab provides a free meal to a person in need, locally. DOWNLOAD THE TANGOTAB APP HERE > Download.TangoTab.com

*** How does Feed The City work? ***
Please arrive between 8:30 am and 9:00 am. We will begin PROMPTLY at 9 am.

Who Can Attend: Anyone is at our events! We make this a fun atmosphere for all ages. Remember, you are responsible for anyone under 18y/o that is in your group.

How to Dress: We would love if you wore orange (but not required), make sure your hair is pulled back, so it doesn't hang in your face or wear a ball cap, wear anything you can get bleach spots on.

*** WHAT TO BRING ***

We request that each person attending is You can bring any of the items in any combination, but this is what we recommend...

• 3 Packs of Meat: Please try to make this turkey, chicken or ham; Unfortunately, we cannot accept any meat from the deli counter

• 3 packs - 16 slices each of cheese (no spicy cheese please!)

• 4 Loaves of bread: Try to find a loaf that has 20 slices (not including the ends); Btw we definitely prefer wheat

• 1 Mustard - plain yellow

• 1 bag of Halos, Cuties or tangerines

• 1-2 bags of chips

• 1 - 100 ct. of Sandwich Bags (make sure they zip)

PLEASE TRY TO BRING AN EQUAL AMOUNT OF MEAT, CHEESE & BREAD. Example: If you bring enough slices of cheese for 72 sandwiches, bring enough meat and bread for 72 sandwiches.

REMEMBER, AT THE END OF THE DAY WE WANT TO PRODUCE QUALITY OVER QUANTITY. Please focus on the product you are buying and not just the amount.

events.name: Artist-Tree Workshop: Overstory + Understory
events.description_html:
End your Earth Week 2020 the right way by joining TreeFolks and Ann Armstrong for a FREE, live art workshop through Zoom!

Is there a tree in your yard (or close by) that you’d like to get to know better?* Or are you curious about trees in general? Consider participating in Over Story + Under Story. The two-part virtual meetup, led by Austin artist and Odditree Society founder Ann Armstrong, revolves around observing a tree of one’s choosing over the course of a week. The week of lightly guided observation will be bookended by an initial digital meetup meeting to discuss the intent and underpinnings of the project, and a second to circle back to see what participants discovered and documented. This arboreal exploration aspires to: augment our connection to and awareness of our surrounding environment, create time and space for discovery, and expand this discovery through collective exploration/sharing of resulting travel guides.

*If you don’t have safe and convenient access to a tree at this time, we encourage you to revisit a tree from memory!

Participants must sign up here: https://www.treefolks.org/event/artist-tree-workshop-with-anne-armstrong/

This Workshop has limited spots! Please sign up at the link above and you will receive further instructions to join the workshop!

Learn more about Ann Armstrong here: ann-made.org

events.description_html:
The Green New Deal
Dates Saturdays, remaining sessions April 25, May 2, 10 am—12 pm
Location via Zoom videoconferencing
Facilitated by Adam Wasserman and Jean Darling
Sponsored by Adult Lifelong Learning and Environmental Justice Teams
​Cost none
Class size limit: 12

This class will look at a range of comprehensive responses to the climate crisis, particularly the Green New Deal and similar proposals. We will examine the pros and cons of the alternatives and discuss their implications for New Mexico, the US, and the world. We will look at the most important concrete steps we can take to reduce greenhouse gases. Drawing on what we learn, we will ask: How can we help mobilize public opinion in favor of immediate and meaningful action? For each session there will be a short reading; during class, we will watch video talks together and then discuss key questions.

El evento dura dos horas, los participantes hacen parte de una serie de conversaciones 2-a-2 o 2-a-1 o 1-a-2 o 1-a-1 que duran en total 24min: 12min en inglés y después 12min en español luego los participantes cambian de mesa virtual y conocen a dos nuevos Spanglishers. events.description_html:
• What we'll do
***************
We will spend a little time getting to know each other, and begin exploring the scope and direction of our discussions. The list of topics to consider is broad, and together we will narrow the field to a few most popular issues to focus on. As we move into the discussions, expect robust and energizing conversation that will peel back the layers of our topic and help us move to the core of the important issues we decide to address.

We recognize that we sometimes don't agree with the opinions or beliefs of others who choose to join us; however, the diverse discussion that develops is encouraged. Contemplative conversations are not debates. Instead, we seek to understand, then be understood. To support this effort, we strongly discourage unfounded conspiratorially charged dialogue.

events.name: Could Jesus have had alliances with any Jewish and Roman leaders? Part 1
events.description_html:
In one of our last in-person meetings, we considered questions about Jesus' wealth, leadership skills, and the breadth of his influence during his own lifetime. In recent times some scholars such as John Dominic Crossan argue that Jesus was just a peasant with very little influence in his own lifetime and that he died as a common, practically unknown insurrectionist. However upon reexamining the evidence we found that if Jesus started out poor and unknown, he and his family didn’t end that way.

Nothing more attests to his humble beginnings than the well-attested claim that he was from Nazareth, a very small and poor village. Yet it seems that during his lifetime he was able to win the financial backing of certain wealthy people, including from a family of the manager of domestic affairs of the ruler Herod Anitpas (Luke 8:3). There is such a high quantity of unrelated stories from various independent sources (e.g. Q, Mark, and John) that it seems historically likely that Jesus was well known and supported by certain people of power, for example: certain tax professionals (who represent a class of society well above poverty); a rich man named Joseph of Arimathea; and a powerful Pharisee named Nicodemus (though no corroborating evidence of him is found outside of the Gospel of John). And after Jesus’ death the historian Josephus indicates that Jesus’ brother/cousin James was a very influential figure in the Jewish Temple in Jerusalem, which sociologically speaking, was a very long way away from Nazareth. If Jesus’ family started out poor, the evidence suggests that they acquired significant status during Jesus’s and James’s lifetimes.

In our next live meeting, we will continue down this line of questioning and discuss the following:

1. Could the relationship between the families, the "House of Caiaphas" and the "House of Jesus," be described as a feud? Did the High Priest Caiaphas consider Jesus a direct threat? Is Caiaphas' family responsible not only for the execution of Jesus, but also the execution of his brother/cousin, James?

2. Did Jesus, in fact, have any alliances with certain Jewish and Roman leaders, perhaps with some who would have benefited from the removal of Caiaphas' family from the Jerusalem Temple?

3. What divisions and alliances were forming in elite Roman circles at this time, and could Jesus have had any participation in them?

Join us for what guarantees to be a thoughtful discussion!

events.name: Late Start: The Value in Struggling to Become a Generalist
events.description_html:
In the late ninth century, Caliph al-Ma’mun commissioned a measurement of Earths circumference. Al-Ma’mun dispatched two groups to the desert to find a specific location by following the stars. One group walked north and the other south, tracking the stars for one degree. They counted their paces and then walked back and averaged the measurement. The two groups then multiplied by 360 to derive a circumference of 24,480 miles. The modern value is 24,901 miles - less than 2% more accurate than the determination of al-Ma’mun and his team. In physics Fermi's order of estimation (named after physicist Enrico Fermi) teaches approximation via the “back of the envelop method.” Fermi estimations typically involve making justified guesses about quantities but are often accurate when using logic to deduce a solution. These calculations are accurate because the methods lack consistent bias. But whether its Femi's order of estimation or Caliph al-Ma’mun’s measurement of the Earths circumference, the ability to make these assertions stems from a generalized understanding of the world.

This raises an enduring and intriguing question: is developing a broad set of interests and skills more effective than focusing on and excelling in one area? The book “Range” examines some of the world’s most effective people and claims generalists, not specialists, are better primed to excel. Author David Epstein asserts that a broad range of interests nurturers creativity and results in a greater ability in deducing meaningful connections. From professional athletes to Nobel laureates, the author claims early specialization is the exception, not the rule when excelling professionally.

Epstein even uses himself as an example, stating he committed “statistical malpractice” while earning his master’s degree. While studying geology in grad school, he feels that having focused on narrow specialized information, without understanding the underlying processes, impeded his ability to discern the root cause of the problem his research aimed to solve. More broadly, Epstein attributes the pervasive replication crisis plaguing science to the narrowly focused specialization among researchers.

Another reoccurring theme is limited experiences create bias that in turn diminishes the capacity to make accurate judgments. Conversely, those enjoying diverse ranges of experiences tend to have a greater opportunity to develop more nuanced understanding of reality. Those who are specialized may tend to be more narrowly focused, impeding their ability to process new information/data in a meaningful manner. People who proactively step outside their area of expertise can see “the big picture”, which is often required for developing sound judgment. Generalists can draw on a large array of sources to test their ideas/hypotheses which would be more difficult with a narrowly focused view of the world.

We will discuss the pros and cons associated with being a generalists.

Resources:

Range Ted Talk: How Falling Behind Can Get You Ahead | David Epstein | TEDxManchester
: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BQ2_BwqcFsc

Range: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-61Y7ytK6zc

In Praise of Misfits: https://www.economist.com/business/2012/06/02/in-praise-of-misfits

Questions to think about?

Do you think it’s better to be a generalists or to specialize in a specific area?

What are some the benefits of being a generalists?

What are some the advantages come with specialization?

Is it better to be “interested” in a wide range of things and not know what we do?

What are the tradeoffs in having a broad set of interest’s vs specializing in a specific area?

How has industrialization impacted our ability to be generalists?

I am adding one additional video for your edification but it is unlikely we’ll have time to cover its contents: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ST6XEDcD_C4

events.name: HAT Forum - "Was Thomas Malthus Chicken Little?"
events.organiser: Humanist Association of Toronto (HAT) Meetup Group
events.description_html:
The Humanist Association of Toronto
http://www.humanisttoronto.ca/

Every Saturday we meet to discuss a topic decided upon the previous week. These are topics of humanist interest, from a humanist perspective.

The topic of the discussion will be decided in a prior meeting, usually two weeks in advance. This week’s topic is: "Was Thomas Malthus Chicken Little?"

In 1798, the English cleric and economist Thomas Malthus published An Essay on the Principle of Population. He wrote that “the increase of population is necessarily limited by the means of subsistence,” “population does invariably increase when the means of subsistence increase,” and “the superior power of population is repressed by moral restraint, vice, and misery.”

Malthus’s notion that population growth would outstrip the food supply has been proven to be wrong over the last two centuries. There were two things that Malthus missed:

1) Human ingenuity would raise the productivity of agriculture to more than meet the needs of a growing population.

2) Abundance actually lowers fertility rates, rather than raise them as Malthus assumed. Fertility rates have fallen dramatically around the globe, so much so that some demographers are predicting that the world’s population will peak at 11 billion and then decline.

Yet, to this day, Malthusian thinking is still prevalent in some circles.

Discussion Questions

1) Does Malthusianism have any merit?

2) Why do Malthusian predictions persist?

3) Sadly, there are still some people today that face food shortages. Is this due to shortages in the capacity to produce food, the production of food, or are there other factors at play?

4) Why are people today around the world having fewer children than their ancestors?

5) Has urbanization played a role in the failure of Malthusianism?

Meet our diverse group, trade perspectives in a free and open forum and learn from others as they learn from you!

BTW: our online meetings have been very popular. Many HAT members attend regularly but don’t sign up on Meetup so there are usually more attendees than sign ups. Please keep your RSVP up to date and try to sign in a bit before 11 a.m. as we will be assigning attendees to smaller break-out groups for the first part of the discussion.

NOTE: The HAT Forum adheres strictly to the City of Toronto Policy on Non-Discrimination (http://www.the519.org/public/content/policy-files/The519SpaceUsePolicy.pdf)

Our Website (http://www.humanisttoronto.ca/)

N.B. Members of the group often continue in a more social vein at a local lunch place until 2:30 or so. The lunches are suspended during COVID-19.

events.name: KubeFlow +Keras/TensorFlow 2.0 +TF Extended (TFX) +Kubernetes +Airflow +PyTorch

events.description_html:
**Title**
Hands-on Learning with KubeFlow + Keras/TensorFlow 2.0 + TF Extended (TFX) + Kubernetes + SageMaker + PyTorch + XGBoost + Airflow + MLflow + Spark + Jupyter + TPU

RSVP: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/full-day-workshop-kubeflow-kerastensorflow-20-tf-extended-tfx-kubernetes-pytorch-xgboost-airflow-tickets-63362929227

**Description**
In this workshop, we build real-world machine learning pipelines using TensorFlow Extended (TFX), KubeFlow, and Airflow.

Described in the 2017 paper, TFX is used internally by thousands of Google data scientists and engineers across every major product line within Google.

KubeFlow is a modern, end-to-end pipeline orchestration framework that embraces the latest AI best practices including hyper-parameter tuning, distributed model training, and model tracking.

Airflow is the most-widely used pipeline orchestration framework in machine learning.

**Pre-requisites**
Modern browser - and that's it!
Every attendee will receive a cloud instance
Nothing will be installed on your local laptop
Everything can be downloaded at the end of the workshop

**Location**
Online

**Agenda**
1. Create a Kubernetes cluster
2. Install KubeFlow, Airflow, TFX, and Jupyter
3. Setup ML Training Pipelines with KubeFlow and Airflow
4. Transform Data with TFX Transform
5. Validate Training Data with TFX Data Validation
6. Train Models with Jupyter, Keras/TensorFlow 2.0, PyTorch, XGBoost, and KubeFlow
7. Run a Notebook Directly on Kubernetes Cluster with KubeFlow
8. Analyze Models using TFX Model Analysis and Jupyter
9. Perform Hyper-Parameter Tuning with KubeFlow
10. Select the Best Model using KubeFlow Experiment Tracking
11. Reproduce Model Training with TFX Metadata Store and Pachyderm
12. Deploy the Model to Production with TensorFlow Serving and Istio
13. Save and Download your Workspace

**Key Takeaways**
Attendees will gain experience training, analyzing, and serving real-world Keras/TensorFlow 2.0 models in production using modern frameworks and open-source tools.

events.name: Stash busting sewalong, step 4: sewing up!
events.description_html:
If you're still with me on using a stash fabric or just want general support of your current sewing project here's the last part of this sewlong: sew it up!

If you finished your item long ago, how about making another one? The more of our stash fabrics we get through, the more experience we gain and the more satisfying the sewing process can become.

I must admit that I have not yet started the navy/cream velvet top I want to make - and that's because I am not sure that I picked a suitable pattern. I did start a sleeveless blouse with a different stash fabric (nothing to do with the velvet project just because I got the sudden urge). And I started a toile out of a newly bought and very cheap black jersey so I can evaluate the Lekala pattern I was going to use for my precious velvet. I also used a grey jersey fabric from my stash for a simple raglan sleeved top and now wonder if that mightn't be the best pattern for the velvet?

Every practical bit that I get to do teaches me what works and what doesn't. Unfortunately I often stop at the stage of "oh crikey I've run into a problem" and never picked the project back up. That gets very frustrating. It makes such a nice change this time: I threw myself into sewing with any fabric and any pattern that mysteriously made its way onto my sewing table. I will tackle the velvet, I promise!

What are you making, what kinds of stash fabric have you used recently and which do you think you might use next? Pictures please!

4. If you have a Paypal account, simply log in, and pay as you normally would via Paypal.

Refund & Ticket Resell

All sales are final. We only refund the full amount, if the event is canceled. If it is rescheduled, we will send an email to those who RSVPed 'YES' advising that. A full refund will be given to those that let us know within 2 calendar days of the update email, if you are unable to make it on the new date. No refunds will be given after that time.

However, you can sell your ticket to someone else if you are unable to attend. Please, feel free to post in the comment box for the event, that you have a ticket for sale. Work out payment between yourselves, and have the seller only send the organizer a message letting us know the full name of the person taking your spot. You must let us know two hours before the RSVP close time, on the day of the event.

events.name: Online/Virtual SPEED DATING (30s & 40s) NY Tri-State
events.description_html:
*REGISTER - https://www.weekenddating.com/event-details.aspx?id=7638#tix (our last one sold out quickly so if you'd like participate, please register ASAP)

Meet singles from the safety and comfort of your own home. This event is for Ages 30s & 40s who live or work in NY Tri-State area.

You will meet singles via your computer with webcam or smartphone/tablet (strong WiFi connection required if using a phone). The event will take place in a Virtual Room using Zoom (Zoom is a free download and super easy to use).

HOW DOES IT WORK?
We will break participants into pairs of two, just like we do with traditional speed dating. You will get to speak to each dates for a specified amount of time (typically 4-6 minutes). After the specified number of minutes, the guys will rotate to the next date and the process continues.

Just like with traditional speed dating, at the end of the event you will be able to let us know who you were interested in. We will send you both mutual matches (you picked them and they picked you) as well as one way matches (they picked you but you did not pick them).

You are given 20 minutes from the end of the event to let us know who you are interested in and will receive the results the same night (usually within one hour) or the next morning. You will not have to wait 24 hours or more to get your results.

The minimum number of potential dates will be 5 and the maximum will be about 10. If there are less than 5 members of the opposite sex in attendance, you would get credit for a future Virtual event.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How do I find the Virtual/Zoom Room?
After you purchase your ticket, you will get a confirmation appear on your screen along with the Zoom link for you to use to log in.

*To attend, get ticket at - https://www.weekenddating.com/event-details.aspx?id=7638#tix

*Cost is between $20-$25 depending on how early you register.

events.name: Swift Networking Online! Make Your Business Stand Out
events.description_html:
How to Make Your Business Stand Out from the Crowd of Competitors

Most forward-thinking companies are familiar with the benefits of using social media. If you’re tired of being overlooked then it's time to seek a fresh way to share ideas and have your voice heard.

You can write the content yourself and/or involve employees to regularly contribute. Sometimes it’s a good idea to have someone else handle this task. You want to concentrate on producing high-quality content. Purely promotional media will drive people away, while insightful, entertaining and educational content will attract them.

Hello Business Professionals,

Please join us for an evening of Swift Networking

Network with as many people as possible in one evening. If it looks like you're spending too long with one person then you will be given the signal to move onto the next person.

600_[masked].jpeg

6 pm: Arrive for mix and mingle

6.30 pm: Guest Speakers - Chi Odogwu (Media Consultant), Peter Kelly (Video Producer & Editor) and Andrea Ivanka (International Coach & Speaker)

Chi Odogwu - How to leverage podcast guest appearances to grow your business

Appearing as a guest on top-rated podcasts can help business owners increase their visibility and authority and help them attract clients for their products and services. Chi will discuss the benefits of this PR strategy and why entrepreneurs, executives, and thought leaders need to get started today.

Peter Kelly - Why video is the most effective way to market your business, and how to get started using just your smartphone.

In this talk Peter will spend 5 minutes explaining how video is the fastest growing marketing tool and why it is effective, 5 minutes on how small businesses can best utilize this; regardless of their budget and 10 minutes showing practical tips on how to create a video with a smartphone, even if you've never made one before. He will also provide free access to an online interactive tutorial that expands on the tips he has shared.

Andrea Ivanka - 3 things you should know when marketing to women

Women are gaining a place in the marketplace and are a key decision in buying, learn how to market to them.

7.30 pm - Swift Networking: Spend about five minutes with each business professional then move onto the next person.

You save your time by meeting several people in a short space of time rather than spending the entire evening in conversation with the same set of people.

By the end of the evening, you will have several useful contacts to pursue.

Cost: $13 per person online https://bit.ly/2R3jkOM

Zoom event will only be accessible to those with an online ticket.

I'm really looking forward to meeting everyone.

Please feel free to contact email me with comments and questions anytime through my profile.

Sam

events.name: Kontinuierliche Weiterentwicklung der Arbeitsweise
events.organiser: COVID19: Für die Zukunftsfähigkeit der Organisationen lernen
events.description_html:
Den Auftakt unserer Veranstaltungsreihe starten wir mit dem Thema „Kontinuierliche Weiterentwicklung der Arbeitsweise“.

Aufgrund der veränderten Marktsituation sind alle derzeit gefordert, die bestehenden Arbeitsweisen der neuen Situation anzupassen. Die einen können ins Homeoffice umziehen, die anderen müssen ihren Arbeitsplatz modifizieren. Insgesamt kristallisieren sich überall neue Arbeitsroutinen und-strukturen heraus. Wir befinden uns inmitten eines umfassenden Transformationsprozesses, welcher durch die aktuelle Pandemie massiv beschleunigt wurde.

Wie sieht das in Ihrem Unternehmen aus? Welche Art Weiterentwicklung der Arbeitsweise findet bei Ihnen statt? Wie lernen Sie gerade mit dieser Situation umzugehen?

In diesem kostenfreien Online-Workshop möchten wir gemeinsam mit Ihnen an der Zukunftsfähigkeit von Unternehmen arbeiten und Ihnen Wege aufzeigen, wie man die Lernfähigkeit der aktuellen Krisensituation dauerhaft verankern kann.

Aufbauend auf diesem und den weiteren Einführungsworkshops wird es die Möglichkeit geben explizite Vertiefungsworkshops zu besuchen.

events.name: Fashion Law and Marketing (Online)
events.description_html:
The textile and clothing sector constitutes a major segment in the European manufacturing industry and plays an essential role in the EU economy as such and in the social welfare of its consumers. Over the years, the EU has developed a wide body of consumer protection law. Conveying accurate information to consumers can limit the scope of misleading or even fraudulent marketing of goods by the fashion industry. This leads to the following question: To what extent does Fashion Law protect consumers against inaccurate or misleading information in fashion marketing and communication?

This online Meetup is part of the #AFAfashiontalks.

Talks:

"Fashion Photography and Neuromarketing"
Robin Hubert, 3rd-year student of the BA (Hons) Fashion with Textiles Design.

Liana Weber: "The future of the European Children Clothing Market"
Liana Weber, 3rd-year student of the BA (Hons) Fashion Business.

Master talk:

"Fashion Law & Marketing Misleading Practices: a concern for consumers?"
Dr. Radha Jethu, Fashion Business programme leader.

Speakers:
Del Johnson – Investment Principal at Backstage Capital
Del Johnson is a venture capital investor, tech writer, and keynote speaker who builds organizations that identify outlier talent beyond the reach of traditional networks and signals. A graduate of Columbia Law School, Del declined his big law firm offer to join Backstage Capital, a VC fund dedicated to eliminating tech disparities through investing in high-potential underrepresented founders. As an investment Principal, Del leads the fund’s scouting, diligence, and operations in New York. To date, his fund has invested over $7 million into over 100 startups led by founders from groups traditionally overlooked by venture capitalists. Del honed his skill for talent identification working with the People

Diana Melencio - VC at WISE Ventures
Venture investor focused on early and growth stage investment opportunities in tech-enabled B2B & DTC companies across sports & entertainment, media, consumer, real estate, and adjacent industries. Previously built and scaled two technology companies in retail and consumer tech: securing funding and successfully leading major partnerships; most notably with the Hudson's Bay Company, Neiman Marcus, MasterCard, and Hearst Media. Prior to starting her companies, Diana spent close to a decade investing and consulting for reputable $12B+ funds in San Francisco and New York.

Mat Kaliski – Principal at Rubicon Venture Capital
Mat is a Principal at Rubicon Venture Capital where he focuses on sourcing, evaluating and supporting portfolio companies. Mat is passionate about building a diverse and inclusive tech community and is a co-organizer of Founders Friday and started FirstGeneration VC.
Rubicon Venture Capital is a generalist fund that invests in Late Seed and Series A rounds of enterprise and omni-channel consumer companies. Rubicon was an early investor in Daily Harvest, Domio, SuperCoffee, EasyKnock, Superhuman and others.

Nicole Shimer - Senior Investment Associate Insight
Nicole Shimer joined Insight in 2016, where she focuses on enterprise SaaS investments across verticals. Prior to Insight, Nicole worked in Morgan Stanley’s Investment Banking Technology Group in NYC. Nicole graduated Phi Beta Kappa and Sigma Xi from Brown University. She is active in the alumni community by sitting on the University’s Advisory Council on Entrepreneurship and leading Digital Brown, an NYC-based and tech-focused alumni group with 600+ members. Outside of work, Nicole is a Yoga Alliance certified yoga teacher and enjoys traveling.

events.name: FASHION BUSINESS VISION BOARD PARTY
events.description_html:
Tired of being isolated at home? Miss socializing with friends? Don't know where your business is headed next?

Most of us are in the same boat so let's do something fun!

LET'S GET TOGETHER FOR THIS FUN VIRTUAL EVENT!!

LEARN HOW TO & CREATE YOUR VERY OWN FASHION BUSINESS VISION BOARD!

SIGN UP HERE: https://fashionvisionboard.eventbrite.com/?aff=Meetup

Vision boards WORK and are great for helping you to get really clear and concise on what your goals are, visualizing your dreams, and turning them into a reality. If you write it down and declare it, it will come to pass!

This event is about empowering one another during this difficult time to continue to reach our goals. It will be hosted by none other than, Christine Daal, one of the top fashion consultants in the industry & Founder of FASHION ANGEL WARRIOR!

She will help you envision your future fashion business goals and continue to plan for all the successful years to come.

You'll get to connect with other like minded fashionpreneurs and create a vision board specifically just for you!

WHAT YOU'll NEED:

- A poster/foam board or virtual board (ie. pinterest or a simple word doc will do)

- Art/Crafting supplies such as markers, glue stick, scissors, etc (not necessary if you're doing a virtual board)

- Pictures, Magazines, tear sheets or a printer if you plan to find your images online (not necessary if you're doing a virtual board)

-A computer and wifi connection so you can join us on zoom

Then grab your favorite drink of choice (alcoholic or not) and get ready to have a Vision Board Party!

WHO IS THE EVENT FOR:

- Anyone who is starting or has an existing fashion line or boutique

- Anyone who is just starting their fashion career, either as a student or designer

- Anyone who is serious and committed to making their fashion dreams happen!

WHERE: ZOOM

WHEN: THURSDAY APRIL 30,2020

TIME: 8pm - 9pm EST

***FREE OF CHARGE***

**ZOOM LINK WILL BE PROVIDED ONCE SIGNED UP**

(Online event- please download/signup for Zoom prior to event via computer)

WHAT YOU’LL GAIN FROM THIS:

- Mental clarity on your goals

-A clear vision of your brand

-Road map to success

-Self love

-New fashionpreneur friends

In the end, you'll have a powerful vision board ready!

LOOKING FORWARD TO 'SEEING' YOU THERE!! Share this event with others so they can join the fun.

Join Our Online Event at: https://us04web.zoom.us/j/205135066?pwd=V1ZSdkxnZk5wNlZnOTI4S2xkd1ZhQT09

This 30-minute low-impact (no hopping, running or joint-jarring movements) high-intensity workout is sure to wake you up and get your day started with a bang!

This class is designed with beginners and older adults in mind. The low-impact exercises help to lower the risk of aches & pains in the joints during the workout. Therefore, you can focus on the workout and allow the muscles to take on all the suffering...in a good way!

You will go through a series of dynamic body movements abiding by a timed interval sequence using anything and everything we have at our disposal. Work at your own pace. Let your body acclimate to the program. The more often you show up the better your body adapts. After a few workouts crank it up and really burn off those pesky extra calories.

events.name: Saturday AM run Hermann/Rice run starting at Centennial Gardens main entrance
events.description_html:
COVID19 Update: We are still meeting, but we are less "groupy" than we used to be for the time being. We are observing social distancing at all times and are trying not to run as a big group in order to ensure adequate spacing for other runners along the route. It is highly advised to bring your own water because some of our water stops are not operational and that is may not change for a few months. Stay healthy!

The most important thing is to find us! I feel bad when people sign up but don't find us and give up. We are always at the concrete marker at the entry to Centennial Gardens (aka Cherie Flores Garden Pavilion). So, Google 'Centennial Gardens' and you should get very close. The concrete marker at the entrance is right by the major parking lot at the north side of Hermann Park.

Since we tend to be a small group (6 to 12 people most times) we mostly run together on a 5 mile loop that includes Hermann Park and a loop around Rice University, which can easily be cut to a 2 mile run, because we loop close to the starting point before heading towards the Rice campus loop. We try to adjust the pace to keep everyone at a light conversational pace as best we can, and there are four working water fountains along the route and in summer we try to visit three.

The combo Hermann/Rice loop is much less crowded than Memorial Park, yet still provides softer crushed gravel trails for our delicate feet, plus the added bonus of being nearly 100% shaded.

Map of course. Red- 2 mile Hermann park portion, yellow- Rice 2.9 mile loop portion. Multiple water fountains available at Miller Outdoor Theatre, Rice Blvd, and University Blvd. Restrooms available at Miller and Centennial Gardens (opens at 9 AM).

Location of Meetup:

Waiting in front of (or sitting on top of) the concrete sign Centennial Gardens as shown below in parking lot C you will most often find members Andy, Evan or Nat - with a rotating cast of occasional runners.

Stephen (pronounced Steff-un), the listed host, is the spiritual guide for the group, rarely physically present but as the originating sponsor his legacy lives on.

We recommend that any interested runners look us up on our sister running group on Facebook that meets every Thursday night at 7pm, the Radar Runners located at Under the Radar Brewery in Midtown.

https://www.facebook.com/groups/RADARRUNNING/

LOCATION for Post-run activities is wherever you want to roam! We used to try to have an organized gathering point but over time that has withered away. However a few of us do tend to clean up after the run and reconvene at Java Lava for the breakfast of champions (bacon, eggs and potatoes for me with a latte, but Nat prefers a nice Pilsner).

Wishing you good running!
