events.name: Cooking class from Italy live via Zoom! Eggplant Parmesan - Join us!
events.description_html:
Learn Eggplant Parmesan with Raffaele. Live class from the Campana region in Italy. You can prepare the menu during the class, or you can just observe. Up to you.

Click Link to Join Zoom Meeting
https://zoom.us/j/97780350148?pwd=YkExS1pJdXdTd3R1a2JZUFArMzNBQT09

Meeting ID:[masked]
Password:[masked]

THE MENU (for 4 people)
Melanzane alla parmigiana
(Parmigina Eggplants)

FOR THE MAIN DISH
3.3 pounds (1,5 kg) eggplants better if the long kind
12 ounces (350 gr) mozzarella fresca
5 ounces (150 gr) grated Parmesan cheese
peanut or other frying oil
fine salt

FOR THE SAUCE
extra virgin olive oil
fresh basil
18 ounces (800 gr) crushed tomatoes (passata di pomodoro)
1/2 onion thinly sliced
salt

Please prepare the following prior to class

1 day prior
Open the fresh mozzarella package, remove the water and put back into fridge to allow to dry a bit.

30 Minutes
Tomato Sauce: Lightly brown the thinly sliced 1/2 onion with some extra virgin olive oil. Add the crushed tomatoes, add a bit of salt, put the cover on and cook at low flame for about 30 minutes. Towards the end, add a couple of basil leaves.
Eggplants: Wash and cut them in thin slices (longwise). Place the slices in a colander, creating a few layers. Put a bit of salt on each layer. At the top, place a weight (for example a pot with water inside) for about 20 minutes to allow more water to come out.

events.name: Central Florida Earth Day!

Central Florida Earth Day is back--bigger and better than ever! It will be held on Saturday, April 25, 2020 from 10:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. at beautiful Lake Eola Park in Orlando. Please join us at the largest and most prestigious Earth Day event in Central Florida.

The event will include healthy living and eco-friendly exhibitors, speakers, and presentations; non-profits; fun and games for kids; dog and cat adoptions; restaurant booths; environmental and humane education; artist and craft corners; and live music and entertainment. Central Florida Earth Day will draw both committed environmentalists and those who want to learn more about how to protect our health, the planet, and its inhabitants. You can promote your business or group to thousands of people who want to learn more about environmentalism and the varied products and services that support an eco-friendly and a veg-friendly way of life. All money raised will be used for local environmental education and outreach.

For more information, visit www.CFEarthDay.org. This website will be continually updated as additional sponsors, vendors, restaurants, speakers, musicians, etc. are added. Please check back often for all the exciting changes! If you are interested in being a vendor, please go the Vendor Packet page. events.name: Good for You & Good for the Earth: a sustainable healthy diet
events.organiser: Eat for the Earth Santa Cruz
events.description_html:
Is it possible to feed our growing human population a healthy diet while simultaneously respecting the environmental limits of our Earth? Can our diets hold the key to reducing the incidence of human disease and helping to prevent worldwide environmental catastrophe? A growing body of research has arisen to answer these questions. The consensus is that it is possible! We can do it, but it will require a radical transformation of global human dietary patterns.

In this webinar, "Good for You and Good for the Earth: How a sustainable healthy diet can make a world of difference," Rev. Beth Love of Eat for the Earth will share about the connections between our diets and the wellbeing of the Earth system. She will be joined by nutrition expert Sandi Rechenmacher, who will illuminate the basics of nutritious eating. It turns out that eating in a way that is good for the earth is also good for you! You will learn about the particular human dietary pattern that holds tremendous benefit for human health, environmental sustainability, and the cause of a world in which all people can be adequately nourished. You will have the opportunity to have your questions answered and to find out how to get involved in the movement for change.

A sustainable healthy diet is good for you, good for the Earth, and confers tremendous additional benefits. Are you ready to reap the rewards?

Note, you can RSVP "yes" here on Meetup to indicate your intent to participate. Please register on our Eventbrite site to be sure you are in the loop for videoconference login information: https://sustainable-healthy-diet.eventbrite.com.

events.name: Immersive Interaction Design Principles Master Class (Sponsor Event)
events.description_html:
*** Sponsored Event!!****

USE CODE XRLA10 FOR 10% OFF

**This does not guarantee entry, please see the eventbrite link for more information! https://www.eventbrite.com/e/immersive-interaction-design-principles-master-class-tickets-102431673894?aff=Meetup&afu=358653131077

About this Event

You will learn the best use cases for applications in VR and how to take full advantage of virtual tools to design an immersive user experience. You will get an overview of good and bad examples of designing user interfaces and interactions in VR.

You will discover the basic concepts of how our brain perceives the world and how to take advantage of it to build the best possible immersive experiences and how to trick your mind into enhancing the experience.
You will understand key principles of responsive VR interactions with buttons, doors, levers, the difference between kinematic and physics-based interactions and objects, and how to use them in the best possible way.

This live & online course consists of 2 parts:

In the first 4 hours, the instructors will explain the Principles of Immersive Interaction Design, including a one hour Q&A session (142 EUR, excl. tax, and fees).

In the second part (duration depending on projects submitted), we will check your personal VR/AR project and give feedback on how to improve interaction design and implementation. Max 5 Participants. The principles that were explained earlier in class will be applied and explained while looking at your project. So you will know exactly what to focus on to improve your project's interaction design level. (241 EUR, excl tax, and fees)

If you are only interested in watching the course content, you can also opt for our recording only ticket. After the course, we will send you a link to the recording and presentation of the immersive interaction design course (First week of May, accessible for at least one month). You will not have the chance to ask questions or interact with the trainers.

Meet Your Instructors

Fascinated by the endless opportunities in VR, Swiss ETH graduates Roger Kung and Dennys Kuhnert founded next-gen VR studio Holonautic in 2018. Their team of seven created Holoception, a new type of hybrid VR game available on Steam and the Oculus Store.Both instructors bring diverse expertise to the table. Roger has a degree in Economics, Life Sciences, and Computer Science, while Dennys has a degree in Bioengineering. With the viral success of their interactive experiments with Oculus Quest hand tracking, they’re excited to share their knowledge and experience with you, and help push beyond the current standards of VR to build the future of spatial computing.

Please download the full agenda here:

https://xrbootcamp.com/inquire-curriculum/

Once we receive your ticket confirmation, we will send you the login information for the course. If you booked the byop option, we will send you a link to submit your personal project for review.

Otus the Omnipotent, former hedge-wizard of High Harbor, now elevated (well, at least in his own mind) to a wizard of serious renown, has absconded with a prized magical artifact to a nearby ruined tower.

Perhaps its time to get back on course.

Note: This game is full, please contact us to see if there is an opening.

events.name: D&D 5E Homebrew:  The Wealth of Nations
events.description_html:
* How to Join *
We are opening this campaign up to new players. Due to the Coronavirus, we are moving this campaign online for the foreseeable future. Please sign onto the Meetup page if you are interested in joining.

*Summary*

A volcanic island has been discovered on the southern coast of the mainland. Control of this volcano and the red crystals within will be key to defining the mainland kingdom as a world power in the years to come. You and your companions are embarking with a military expedition to establish a base of operations on the volcano, and exterminate the monster threat which plague the land.

This is a Hexcrawler across a entire continent. Survive against not just monsters, but the weather, disease, injuries, starvation, thirst, time, and the terrain itself. A open ended adventure for those wanting to explore the unknown.

*Optional Rules*

Energy Crystals: This world has crystals which can store and release the energies of the universe. When a player cast's a spell, they may consume a crystal to change the damage type to a type specified by the crystals type
You may also spend a crystal to change the damage type for all ranged or melee attacks until the end of the round.

Expertise: Your character is a expert in a particular skill. Upon character creation, each character may choose one feat from the UA Skill Feats. (You must be proficient with the skill, and no attribute bonus)
https://media.wizards.com/2017/dnd/downloads/UA-SkillFeats.pdf

Environmental Hazards: I will be designing new terrain to add variety to combat.

Flanking (+2): Instead of advantage, flanking provides a +2 to hit.

Action Options: Climb onto a bigger creature
Action Options: Disarm
Action Options: Overrun
Action Options: Shove Aside
Encumbrance (I will do the bookkeeping, but feel free to double check)
Equipment Sizes
Feats
Firearms, Explosives (Renaissance Only)
Hitting Cover
Injuries
Disease
Massive Damage
Flanking (+2)

*Restrictions*

No Evil Races

Race needs to pass as human - People in the city states are xenophobic, especially with the discovery of a humanoid monster on the island. Non humans are being purged from society, so the PC must be able to pass for human.

No Outlander background. The wildlife outside the cities makes living in the wilds nigh impossible.

*Changes*

Goodberry consumes its material component
Foraging only brings enough food and water for one person.
The Rangers "Natural Explorer" Ability is reworked with the following abilities.
- Advantage on Navigation Checks
- Advantage on Perception Checks
- When you forage for food, you can feed an additional person.

events.name: Private FREE Arena Draft - Ikoria
events.description_html:
Everyone meet up in discord: https://discord.metamox.com in the #washington-dc channel

The only rule is that you need to have enough cards in Arena or enough wildcards to convert whatever card you pick. If you've played a few drafts, you realistically aren't going to need many wildcards, but if you're a limited-only player, this is basically the only way to burn those wildcards you'll otherwise never use.

Make sure you have Arena downloaded, account created, and the app loaded.

Greg

events.name: Book Three Review: "The Murmur of Bees" - Sofia Segovia
events.organiser: The Tampa Bay Friends Of Dorothy Book Club
events.description_html: From a beguiling voice in Mexican fiction comes an astonishing novel--her first to be translated into English--about a mysterious child with the power to change a family's history in a country on the verge of revolution. From the day old Nana Reja found a baby abandoned under a bridge, the life of a small Mexican village forever changed. Disfigured and covered in a blanket of bees, little Simonopio is for some locals the stuff of superstition, a child kissed by the devil. But he is welcomed by landowners Francisco and Beatriz Morales, who adopt him and care for him as if he were their own. As he grows up, Simonopio becomes a cause for wonder to the Morales family, because when the uncannily gifted child closes his eyes, he can see what no one else can--visions of all that's yet to come, both beautiful and dangerous. Followed by his protective swarm of bees and living to deliver his adoptive family from threats--both human and those of nature--Simonopio's purpose in Linares will, in time, be divined. Set against the backdrop of the Mexican Revolution and the devastating influenza of 1918, The Murmur of Bees captures both the fate of a country in flux and the destiny of one family that has put their love, faith, and future in the unbelievable.

events.name: Feeling emotionally challenged? Join our therapist facilitated discussion
events.description_html:
I know that many of us have our "normal" set of things that unsettle us and contribute to feeling stressed and down. However, this time now is unprecedented so there is no roadmap on how we "should" be feeling or grappling with the state of affairs locally and globally. Our health is at risk, our financial futures are at risk and here we are stuck in our own little worlds inside. Hopefully your home feels safe to you.

I have invited a very close friend and excellent, compassionate Marriage & Family Therapist, Robin Stuart to lead a discussion to help navigate our feelings through these times. She has over 30 years experience in supporting and guiding people to better embrace where they are now as well as finding new possibilities for brighter days tomorrow.

We want you to feel safe to join this meeting so you have the option of leaving your videos off and creating a nickname on your zoom profile if you like. You don't even need to RSVP here if you are not comfortable although I think it will be easier for others to sign up if there are some people to get it started.

Robin will set some structure and guidelines for the discussion similar to those in a group therapy session including a verbal confidentiality agreement and will be leading the discussion.

This is a good time to share your vulnerability and challenges with others who can relate. This will not be like our happy hour where we chat, tell jokes and play games... This is a space to give and receive support while a safe space is being held.

Please note: The discussion on this day is free of charge and is not considered an official client/therapist relationship. However, after this week, Robin will be offering an opportunity to continue on with her in a group for a very manageable fee.

I HOPE YOU WILL JOIN US IF YOU FEEL THIS DISCUSSION WILL PROVIDE VALUE

ZOOM APP- Meeting I.D. [masked] or simply click this link to use your web browser https://zoom.us/j/3877685410
PASSWORD: smwslt

Let's do some crafts together ON THE INTERNET! This is not limited to just sewing, I just want to call it a sewing circle. Do whatever craft you want! We've had people sew, knit, crochet, work on things on their computers, color, or just hang out and chat. Do whatever project you're working on or none at all!xt

Unfortunately I won't be able to share supplies because we'll be remote but even if you're just there to chat and hangout, that's great! Just getting to spend time together while we're all stuck inside is awesome.

events.name: Online: Community Check-In & Crazy Sexy Love Notes!
events.description_html:
Even though we can't be together in our studio or over brunch, we can check-in to see how we are all coping with the pandemic and share laughs and insights as we read cards from the "Crazy Sexy Love Notes" deck.

Grab a cup of your favorite tea or java and connect with your yoga family for a 1-hour video chat.

How To Connect:

You may connect with video and audio or just audio and stay for as long or as short a time as your schedule allows.

We will be using the free video-conferencing app, Lifesize, which requires a small download to your computer or app on your phone. You can install and set up Lifesize in advance.

PC/Mac/Laptop
(Please allow 10 minutes to get things up and running.)
1. Create a free Lifesize account: https://signup.lifesize.com/
2. On the next screen, click on the blue "Get Started" button.
You will be prompted to download and run a small file which will connect you to the meeting. (Always a good idea to have as few computer programs as possible running so that your system has sufficient resources to video-conference.)
3. Allow access to your webcam and microphone and use the test page to make sure these components are working correctly.
4. On your Home page where it says "Welcome Your Name! What would you like to do?" click on the "Call" icon and enter the number[masked]
Then click right below on the line that reads: #[masked] Custom Call.
5. Click either "Start with Camera On" (for video) or "Start with Camera Off" (for audio only.)

Mobile App (Please allow 10 minutes to get things up and running.)
1. First create a free Lifesize account: https://signup.lifesize.com/
2. Go to Google Play Store or Apple App Store and download "Lifesize Video Conferencing" app.
3. Allow it to record video and audio.
4. Sign in with your email and password created during Step 1.
5. Click "Profile" then "Settings" and turn on "Favorites," "Chat," and "Chat Notifications."
6. Go back to the Profile Screen.
7. Click "Meet" and then click on the Search (magnifying glass) icon and enter the number[masked]
8. Click either the camcorder (full video) or headphones (just audio) icon to enter the meeting.

events.name: LGBT 🏳️‍🌈 VIRTUAL [on ZOOM] Discussion Group 🏳️‍🌈
events.description_html:
We welcome you to our (NOW VIRTUAL ONLINE - via "ZOOM") monthly discussion group!

Our group last met before pandemic (BP). With all that is going on in our lives, now in pandemic (IP), surely we have MUCH on our minds to discuss!

Topics are chosen in a democratic way by the group with the aim of examining what is working or not working in our lives, and finding ways to live more fully. Topics often come out of our unique lived experiences as LGBT men and women.

The group has agreed to abide by the following guidelines:

- We agree to maintain confidentiality
- Begin each meeting mutually agreeing to a topic and to stay on that topic, unless there is mutual agreement to change the topic as meeting progresses
- No topic is off-limits and each person has the right to speak their mind
- We agree to respect the opinions of others and the right to respectfully disagree
- Absolutely no interrupting of another while they are sharing
- Don't be afraid to take risks
- The responsibility for upholding group principles will be shared equally by all participants
- Participants fairly use the group's time to express their ideas
- Share responsibility for time-keeping and recapping the main take-away approximately 30 minutes before end of each meeting.

events.name: On The Plus+ Side (Online Community Discussion)
events.description_html:
A community discussion to focus on how it feels to identify with the + in LGBT acronyms.

LGBT+? LGBTQ+? LGBTQIA+? What it's like to be someone who feels represented or misrepresented by the plus sign? A supportive and kind discussion to learn about each other’s identities a bit more.

There might be language or labels out there that we don't know about or that we don't understand why they are not included in LGBT acronyms. So let's learn about each other's identities so that we can fully understand why it's important that everybody feels included.

Guest panel to be announced soon.

How to join?

👋 💻 We will be on the video conference app Zoom.

Register a free space at www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/on-the-plus-side-online-community-discussion-tickets[masked]

We will then email you a reminder with the Zoom meeting link, 24 hours before the event. You don't need a Zoom account to access the meeting, just visit the link on the day and time of the event.

events.name: What Form of Government Do We Want?
events.description_html:
This is now an online event
Join Zoom Meeting
https://zoom.us/j/96417417443

Meeting ID:[masked]

There are many important criteria for defining what a government should do for us that would best satisfy our vision of a well-run country, and we could meet for years in the effort to come up with such a definition. With that in mind, I think it’s still worth doing whatever we can. Every bit of personal clarity is worth having, whether we want to solve the world’s problems, or just want to have a better idea of what those problems are in each others’ minds.

We won’t so much discuss what policies need to be changed, as we'll determine how the current federal government is involved in providing us with essential resources, services, and protections, and how each of us would prefer those resources, services, and protections to be provided. The way you feel about how a government should do right by you is probably informed by loftier principles, and my hope is that this exercise will reveal some of those principles in each of us. It’s an attempt at enabling us to better understand each other.

Although there are many different types of government, as Americans we largely tend to see our own constitution and the way it manifests itself as a tug-of-war between Socialist and Capitalist concepts: Medicare, Social Security, and Veterans Affairs are Socialistic, and private ownership and the profit motive are Capitalistic. So let’s find out where we really stand along that scale with respect to various resources, services, and protections.

The spectrum of federal government involvement we’re considering range from “Hands off,” in which you (and your locality) are on your own, no national government participation whatsoever, to “All in,” in which the federal government controls and provides all aspects of a resource (goods and services). We’ll be able to aggregate our individual preferences and generate weighted scores in 15 – 20 categories.

I've provided a Google Docs preview of the criteria we'll be evaluating for this event: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1RLXtWazVJJt0amW5FbYFH0yFqq4kry76qDqzuLSeQ0I/edit?usp=sharing

events.name: UTLP 2020 State/Nominating Digital  Convention
events.description_html:
The Utah Libertarian Party Executive Committee has made a decision to hold our 2020 nominating convention in an online format.

We very much regret not being able to hold a convention in person this year. However, the circumstances we face tell us this is the right thing to do for now. Our guests from around the country face travel restrictions that make their attendance very difficult if not impossible. Here at home, some of our members have medical conditions that compromise their resistance to disease, and we do not wish to endanger any of them. The continuing political uncertainty has wreaked havoc on planning, and while we still hope that by April 25th it will appear this was unnecessary, we feel it is better to have a clear plan going forward from today.

We will be announcing more specifics over the next week as a few details get ironed out, and we will be in touch with all members in good standing with the appropriate new registration links and contact information. It is our intent to move national candidate presentations off the program and onto the website, and have the only candidates making presentations during the convention being those seeking Utah offices. We will have the opportunity to nominate Utah candidates, and conduct other internal party business. We also still intend to conduct a presidential candidate and LNC Chair preference poll, for which details will be announced soon.

If you have purchased either lunch during the convention or a ticket to the Friday night reception, we will be offering a refund if you wish. Details will be emailed soon to those who made purchases.

Stay strong, stay safe, stay healthy. We are disappointed that we will not gather in person this year, but remain focused on nominating and promoting our candidates for office, and most importantly on promoting the ideals of liberty and the fundamental value of every unique individual, the real backbone of a vibrant, thriving nation.

events.name: Peaceful Protest at Texas Capitol in Austin
events.description_html:
PEACEFUL & SAFE protest begins 1pm Saturday at the Capitol in Austin.
See DOs and DON'Ts below.

"Congress shall make no law... abridging the freedom of speech, or of the press; or the RIGHT OF THE PEOPLE TO PEACEABLY ASSEMBLE..." ~ Bill of Rights, Amendment 1
https://billofrightsinstitute.org/founding-documents/bill-of-rights/

DOs

DO Practice all reasonable precautions related to safety from the virus.
DO Wear a surgical mask, N95 mask, or cloth face covering.
DO Practice social distancing (six feet rule).
DO Bring hand sanitizer and use it frequently, wear nitrile gloves or both.
DO Bring signs and placards.
DO make your sign out of light wood, PVC pipe, cardboard, foam board, or poster board.
DO Bring bust cards (small cards that remind you of your rights and what to say to the police).
DO Bring voice amplification, bullhorn, PA.
DO Bring water, food and snacks.
DO Bring rain and/or sun protection.
DO Bring cameras, phones, and recording devices.
DO Record everything.
DO Notify the press and everyone you know about the rally, and ask them to be there.
DO Wear comfortable shoes and clothing.
DO Wear weather appropriate clothing (warm / cold weather).
DO Consider bringing protective gear, if able (goggles, face shields, knee/elbow pads).
DO Consider bringing head protection, such as a bicycle helmet or hard hat.
DO Prepare a SHORT statement for the press, in case you get interviewed.
DO Prepare to be arrested. I’m not saying you WILL be arrested, but it’s a possibility. You might spend the night in jail.
DO Keep in mind few businesses will be open in that area, meaning possibly nowhere to pee. I just ordered a travel pee cup thing from Amazon that will arrive by Friday. https://smile.amazon.com/gp/product/B01LZMVMXL

DON’Ts

DON’T Bring any weapons of any kind.
DON’T Bring anything that can even be construed as a weapon.
DON’T Bring anything with a point, sharp edge, or that could be used as a club.
DON’T Bring anything that can launch or fire a projectile of any kind.
DON’T make your sign out of anything that could hurt anyone. DON’T use a sharp stick or metal pipe for example.
DON’T make a huge heavy sign that you will have to carry around all day
DON’T act aggressive, threaten, or verbally abuse ANYONE.
DON’T get in a fight with ANYONE.
DON’T use foul or abusive language on your sign.
DON’T yell foul or abusive language or use that kind of language with the press or the police.
DON’T get too close to people you don’t know and that aren’t in your personal group.
DON’T resist arrest. If you are getting arrested, peacefully comply and cooperate.
DON’T damage or deface any property.
DON’T litter.

SUGGESTED SLOGANS
Feel free to make up your own slogan, but here are some ideas:

OPEN TEXAS NOW
OPEN AUSTIN NOW
FREEDOM NOW
WE HAVE RIGHTS
NO STRIKE FORCE JUST WORKFORCE
OUR LIVES OUR CHOICE
NO MORE LOCKDOWN
END THE LOCKDOWN
END LOCKDOWN NOW
THE CONSTITUTION IS NOT CANCELLED
BILL OF RIGHTS, DUH
STAND UP TEXAS
FREE TEXAS
TEXAS BACK TO WORK
TEXAS BACK TO LIFE
WE WANT TO LIVE

More details coming soon. Please be sure to watch your email.
Other resources at https://ClearSay.net

Please spread this around! There is strength in numbers.

events.name: Election 2020: Voter Suppression, Dirty Tricks, Etc.: Video meeting
events.description_html:
If only it were as simple as everyone over 18 showing up and making a choice based on reasonable information and understanding. Here are two books highlighting some of the issues that may affect the 2020 presidential election. The first, on voter suppression, is very well reviewed and has good library availability. The second is brand new and may not be available at the library...but it's got a short shelf life, so I will add it as an option and post some links to summaries.

Carol Anderson
One Person, No Vote: How Voter Suppression is Destroying our Democracy (2018)
368 pages
City library, 5/6 available ; County, 4/7 available
Amazon: https://www.amazon.com/One-Person-Vote-Suppression-Destroying/dp/1635571391/ref=tmm_pap_swatch_0?_encoding=UTF8&qid=&sr=

Richard L. Hasen
Election Meltdown (2020)
208 Pages
City library, not available ; County, four copes on order with one hold
https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0849NPC95/ref=dp-kindle-redirect?_encoding=UTF8&btkr=1

One Person, No Vote Amazon Summary:
PEN/John Kenneth Galbraith Award Finalist, Longlisted for the National Book Award
Best Books of the Year--Washington Post, Boston Globe, NPR, Bustle, NYPL

In her New York Times bestseller White Rage, Carol Anderson laid bare an insidious history of policies that have systematically impeded black progress in America, from 1865 to our combustible present. With One Person, No Vote, she chronicles a related history: the rollbacks to African American participation in the vote since the 2013 Supreme Court decision that eviscerated the Voting Rights Act of 1965. Known as the Shelby ruling, this decision effectively allowed districts with a demonstrated history of racial discrimination to change voting requirements without approval from the Department of Justice.

Focusing on the aftermath of Shelby, Anderson follows the astonishing story of government-dictated racial discrimination unfolding before our very eyes as more and more states adopt voter suppression laws. In gripping, enlightening detail she explains how voter suppression works, from photo ID requirements to gerrymandering to poll closures. In a powerful new afterword, she examines the repercussions of the 2018 midterm elections. And with vivid characters, she explores the resistance: the organizing, activism, and court battles to restore the basic right to vote to all Americans.

Election Meltdown Amazon Summary:
From the nation’s leading expert, an indispensable analysis of key threats to the integrity of the 2020 American presidential election

As the 2020 presidential campaign begins to take shape, there is widespread distrust of the fairness and accuracy of American elections. In this timely and accessible book, Richard L. Hasen uses riveting stories illustrating four factors increasing the mistrust. Voter suppression has escalated as a Republican tool aimed to depress turnout of likely Democratic voters, fueling suspicion. Pockets of incompetence in election administration, often in large cities controlled by Democrats, have created an opening to claims of unfairness. Old-fashioned and new-fangled dirty tricks, including foreign and domestic misinformation campaigns via social media, threaten electoral integrity. Inflammatory rhetoric about “stolen” elections supercharges distrust among hardcore partisans.

Taking into account how each of these threats has manifested in recent years—most notably in the 2016 and 2018 elections—Hasen offers concrete steps that need to be taken to restore trust in American elections before the democratic process is completely undermined.

"This is the first novel by Cheyenne and Arapaho author Tommy Orange. Published in 2018, it opens with an essay by Orange as a prologue, and then proceeds to follow a large cast of Native Americans living in the area of Oakland, California, as they struggle with a wide array of challenges ranging from depression and alcoholism, to unemployment, fetal alcohol syndrome, and the challenges of living with an ethnic identity of being "ambiguously nonwhite." All coalesce at a community pow wow and its attempted robbery.

"The book explores the themes of Native peoples living in urban spaces (Urban Indians), and issues of ambivalence and complexity related to Natives' struggles with identity and authenticity. There There was favorably received, and was a finalist for the 2019 Pulitzer Prize. The book was also awarded a Gold Medal for First Fiction by the California Book Awards."

events.name: Wine Tasting. Look at life thru Rosé colored glasses (White & Red too!!)
events.organiser: ! Jewish Meeting Place ! -- Come and Schmooze a while !!
events.description_html:
You like wine.
You like wine tastings.
You may or may not like quarantine. But you do know you like wine in quarantine.

What if there was a way to combine them? Hmmmmmm. What would that look like?

We may have come up with a picture that works.

Here is how it will work. (the broad brush strokes)

We will provide you 5 bottles of wine. Each being 177ml/6 Oz.
We will provide some experts & have a guided tasting.
We will have it all organized & fabulous.
You will be responsible for purchasing the wine and then logging on at the correct time. And also being open to learning and fun.

Here are the finer details

The Wine
1 white
1 rose
3 red

Cost:
$45 Pick-up in Burbank.
$50 Delivered.
https://tr.im/OnlineWineTasting
Order NEEDS to be in by Tues Midnight for deliver

As indicated you will have 5 bottles of wine. Each being 177ml/6 Oz.
That's 887ml/30 oz wine, or what will equal about 1 1/2 bottles of wine.

Each 6 oz bottle would provide 3 tasting portions. A tasting is normally 2 oz. So you could do this event as a couple or even as 3 people together at home.
A normal glass of wine is about 6 oz. If on your own . . you can do a 2 to 6 oz pour.

Here is what we recommend. Let's make this a special evening.
Make a nice meal https://www.instagram.com/bobblumer/
Put a table cloth under your computer.
Set up two (or more) candles.
Dress in some nice clothes (formal clothes recommended such as a gown or tux).

We will be posting recipes by Bob Blumer to the event page to spurn discussion, and you will get an email compilation 2 days before.

Bob will be joining us to discuss food parings to the wines.

(you can stop reading now unless you are the kind of person who loves details)

*Fiore Grenache Blanc Alexander Valley 2017
*Fille de Joie Pinot Noir Rose Sonoma County 2018
*Strega Merlot Sonoma County 2015
*Piccolo Pettit Verdot Alexander Valley 2016
*Due Vigne (Pettit Verdot/Zin blend. Verdot and Zin are enemies so this is is a complicated mix and blend) Sonoma County 2016

If you want 5 full size regular bottles of these instead of the 6 oz shorties . . . That is available on the link https://tr.im/OnlineWineTasting

The Experts:
Giovanni............The Vintner
Francois............The Vigneron
Bob Blumer.......The Culinarista
Mystery Guest..The Oenophile
Marc.................The Cognoscenti

Giovanni is a crazy Italian & the Vintner of all these wines & has personally crafted them. While he does know wine, and especially his wine . . . we are bringing in an outside Vigneron to cover some the notes better, especially not being personally vested in the wine.

Francois will help discern with the notes and flavor and the education end. A Vigneron has the education of a winemaker, and manages/maintains the vineyard year-round and oversees from crush to fermentation, aging, fining and filtering, bottling. He will be joining us from Napa. Francois comes to us from a VERY well known winery and we are lucky to have him.

events.name: Feminist Film Club: Mrs. America Ep. 1 (Hulu)
events.description_html:
Hi folks!

Hope you're all taking care and feeling well in this time we're living in.

Due to the shelter-in-place order, I figured now is as good a time as any to get together (online!) to talk about some thought-provoking, feminist/women-centered media (TV, movies, documentaries) while many of us are stuck at home.

This group will be meeting via Zoom (https://zoom.us/signup) and the invite will be sent out one day prior to the event.

We'll hang out and talk for 40 minutes (the amount of time available for a free account).

~ NOTE: This is a Womxn's-Only Meetup ~

*********************************

For this week's inaugural hangout, we'll be delving into that most mythologized time for activism -- the 1970s.

The first show we'll be watching is Mrs. America, Episode 1 (Phyllis) that's currently streaming on Hulu.

This limited series is a loose retelling of U.S. feminist fights for the Equal Rights Amendment (and the subsequent backlash from conservative women), electing the first female president, and women's right to legalized abortion -- all issues still on the table and that we're fighting for today.

Let's get together and talk about first impressions, what we appreciated, what pissed us off, etc.

Looking forward to "seeing" you!

*********************************

Trigger Warning: there are a few scenes that deal with sexual harassment/assault.

events.name: Video & Article - "What is Higher Consciousness?"
events.description_html:
** We are NOT meeting in-person at The Wedge this week. **

We are instead meeting virtually via video conference. We're going to practice physical distancing while maintaining social connection.

We'll be using Zoom (www.zoom.us), so you can access the meeting for free via your computer or phone (might need to download an app to access via phone).

This week we will look at the ideas and posibilities of the idea of higher consciousness. How does this fit with your views of the subject?

Link - http://beyondiam.com/what-is-higher-consciousness/

Here is a link to just the video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vqCOss4hqnE&t=200s

The book has many specific exercises to discover and get to the root of our judgements so we can uproot them to help ourselves.

*******************************

We are a group that meets to discuss personal development topics. We believe in open, balanced discussion where all sides and viewpoints can be expressed to maximize the possibility of learning and growth. Respect, balance, Self discipline, integrity, and curiosity are some of the principles we aspire towards to build our community.

We start each Meetup by going around the group and sharing something good that happened in the last week or something you are thankful for. Then we discuss the topic of the week, and after the the first round of open discussion, we check in around the group to get as wide an input as possible.

We also occasionally do activities outside of the regular Saturday morning Meetup. Feel free to join us and suggest activities.

Hope to see you there!

“When you believe it, you've created it, whatever it is”
― Bangambiki Habyarimana (http://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7947977.Bangambiki_Habyarimana), Pearls Of Eternity (http://www.goodreads.com/work/quotes/52362912)

Cheers!
Jon and the Miracle Makers

Whilst there is no fee for this online class, you will need to order the materials directly from Stampin' Up! in order to participate in the class.

You will need to order both the kit and stamp set, these are the details for the separate two items.

For The Love of Felt Project Kit item #[masked] $30.00
For The Love of Felt stamp set item #[masked] $20.00

Please use this link to order online with Stampin' Up! and enter host code ATDVN7KZ.

https://www.stampinup.com/ecweb/default.aspx?dbwsdemoid=2127130

If you add more products to your order, and find that your items total over $150.00 before tax and shipping, please do not use the host code.

PLEASE BE SURE TO ORDER YOUR KIT AND STAMP SET ASAP. Whilst this seems like a long way in advance of when you will need them, with Easter, the slower processing time at Stampin’ Up! and inevitable closure of SU, I want to be sure that you receive your items before the class on April 25.

If you order before March 31, you can also choose free Sale-A-Bration items too!

To complete the cards, you will need ink, ideally Stampin’ Up! Classic ink pads in the following colors: Calypso Coral, Daffodil Delight, Pear Pizzazz, Sahara Sand and Shaded Spruce (alternative colors will work well too) Also, Dimensionals, Multipurpose Liquid Glue and SNAIL adhesive, scissors and clear blocks - ideally b, c and h.

I will also be sending everyone that joins the online class, materials to make an alternative card using the For the Love of Felt stamp set.

The meeting ID for zoom will be emailed to all attendees

Please drop me a line with any questions you might have, and to RSVP. [masked]

I am very excited to stamp with you!
With thanks, Sarah

events.name: Stash busting sewalong, step 4: sewing up!
events.description_html:
If you're still with me on using a stash fabric or just want general support of your current sewing project here's the last part of this sewlong: sew it up!

If you finished your item long ago, how about making another one? The more of our stash fabrics we get through, the more experience we gain and the more satisfying the sewing process can become.

I must admit that I have not yet started the navy/cream velvet top I want to make - and that's because I am not sure that I picked a suitable pattern. I did start a sleeveless blouse with a different stash fabric (nothing to do with the velvet project just because I got the sudden urge). And I started a toile out of a newly bought and very cheap black jersey so I can evaluate the Lekala pattern I was going to use for my precious velvet. I also used a grey jersey fabric from my stash for a simple raglan sleeved top and now wonder if that mightn't be the best pattern for the velvet?

Every practical bit that I get to do teaches me what works and what doesn't. Unfortunately I often stop at the stage of "oh crikey I've run into a problem" and never picked the project back up. That gets very frustrating. It makes such a nice change this time: I threw myself into sewing with any fabric and any pattern that mysteriously made its way onto my sewing table. I will tackle the velvet, I promise!

What are you making, what kinds of stash fabric have you used recently and which do you think you might use next? Pictures please!

Just a few weeks ago it was normal to go out drinking on a weekend night.

Online Happy Hours are becoming more and more popular all over the world. So join the fun with new friends from all over the world while sipping your favorite drink!

Soft drinks/coffee/tea welcome too of course :) ☕️🍹 🍵

As we're expecting lots of friendly people to join we're going to split the group up into smaller breakout groups with a maximum of 5 in each to make conversation easy & comfortable.

Notes :

- You're good to join and leave as you like.

Vancouver Spontaneous.

events.name: Dewey's 24 Hour Read-a-thon
events.description_html:
Dewey’s 24 Hour Read A Thon ( http://www.24hourreadathon.com/ ) is back!! I love doing this event because I get through a book or two in one day.

On April 25th the Challenge of reading ALL DAY long starts. During the bi-annual read-a-thon we will read books, post to our blogs, Facebook and Twitter or Goodreads about our reading, and visit other readers’ blogs. We will also participate in mini-challenges throughout the day to win prizes. (I love that part!) This event happens twice a year, in April and in October. It was created by a book lover named Dewey. The first one was held in October 2007. Dewey died in late 2008. The read-a-thon was renamed to honor its founder in 2009.

On April 25th the Dewey’s 24 Hour Read-A-Thon ( https://www.24hourreadathon.com/october-2019-reader-sign-up/ ) will start at 5 am for California. If you want to learn more and to sign up, click on the link. There is no money involved and it’s purely for the love of reading on your own pace, for as long or as little as you want.

Go to http://www.24hourreadathon.com/ to learn more and to sign up! Every six hours I will (try to) post a reminder for you to check our book club website with the links to the hourly challenge and Mocha Girls Read challenges. Yes! You can win prizes if you join in.

You don't need to have a blog to participate.

This is an online event and the Dewey website is the host site you check in every couple of hours. This is the best event to get through a few books on your nightstand.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

events.name: Online 1/2 Day Spiritual Retreat with Meditation Teacher Leslie Booker
events.description_html:
"What We Can Cultivate During This Global Pandemic"

Join meditation teacher Leslie Booker via Zoom in a a 1/2 Day Retreat to her local spiritual community this weekend!

Sliding Scale $10 - 30 + Teacher Offering
*Payment info will be given out during retreat.
*No one will be turned away for lack of funds

In living through a global pandemic, it might feel like our autonomy and basic freedoms have been taken away. But if we pause and look deeper, we can begin to see that there is space to cultivate and tend to what we are experiencing in our hearts, bodies and minds.

In this half day retreat, we'll turn our attention towards the 10 Paramis (Perfections); with a specific look at Renunciation, Wisdom and Generosity. Creating space for greater benevolence, compassion and tenderness to arise.

ABOUT OUR GUIDE
Booker brings her heart, wisdom, and compassion to the intersection of social justice, yoga, and mindfulness. She offers lectures, workshops, and retreats across the country utilizing social justice principles along with embodied wisdom practices to support the sustainability of front line changemakers, and those in direct service. She has been sharing the practices of mindfulness and yoga to incarcerated and system-involved youth since 2007, currently serving as the Director of Trainings for Lineage Project, and brought mindful yoga and meditation to the 2012 Democratic National Convention. She co-founded the Yoga Service Council at Omega Institute and Urban Sangha Project in NYC. Booker is on faculty with the Prison Mindfulness Institute, Spirit Rock’s Mindful Yoga and Meditation training, and Off the Mat, Into the World.

Learn more about Booker:
https://kripalu.org/presenters-programs/presenters/leslie-booker

Check out our moving conversation:
https://www.facebook.com/BlackWomensAlliance/videos/654334271777612/

events.name: Peak District Day Trip - Cancelled due to Coronavirus
events.description_html:
• What we'll do Enjoy breathtaking panoramic views of the great British countryside on this beautiful trip to the Peak District. Famous for its association with Jane Austen and other famous writers and film sets, its a wonderful place for hiking. We will take a very easy and short climb to the top of Mam Tor and enjoy spectacular views. We will also visit the village of Castleton where there are lovely British pubs and cafes. events.name: Free! 無料! ESL YOGA live-stream Zoom!! Connect with Others
events.organiser: North Vancouver LET'S GO YOGA TIME♥ 一緒にヨガしよ：）
events.description_html:
▶誰でもご参加出来ます！
カルマ（ご奉仕）クラス
Karma (free) Class! Anybody can join my class :)　(English down below)

こういう時だからこそ繋がろう﻿！
1人で不安になる事はない﻿
身体を少し動かすだけで、そういう感情を一掃出来るんですって
ヨガの教えの１つです
一緒に深い呼吸をして﻿
画面を通して一緒の時を過ごす﻿
﻿
ヨガをやった事ある人無い人
どちらでも大丈夫です👌﻿
﻿
あなたの心が心地良さでいっぱいになって欲しいから﻿🤗
いつでも私の心のドアをオープンにしてお待ちしています( ◠‿◠ )

■内容
・30分のクラス
・初めてはお互いに自己紹介
・画面越しに一緒にプラクティス
・日本語と英語でのインストラクション
・最後１０分くらい歓談
﻿

■必要なもの
﻿
・インターネットの繋がるパソコン、タブレット、携帯。（大きな画面で見やすいノートパソコン、タブレットがお勧めです）﻿
・ヨガマット（無ければカーペットの上、フローリングの上でも出来ますが、膝が痛くならない様にバスタオルがあると良い）﻿
﻿
ご参加される場合は先ずこちらのページよりご予約下さいね:)
※セキュリティーの為、ミーティングIDとパスワードは、ご予約後メッセージにて個別にお送りさせて頂きます

▶参加方法

①予約する

②ミーティングIDとパスワードをメッセージBOXから受け取る

③携帯・タブレットでご参加される方は予めZOOM Cloud Meetingのアプリをダウンロードしておいて下さい。（パソコンの方は必要ないです）

④お時間の１０分前くらいになりましたら、ヨガマットを引いて下さい。
（手や足を広げて物が落ちて来ない所、スペースには十分に余裕を持った場所でお願いたします。

⑤そして…

【パソコンの方へ】
こちらをクリックし、アクセスしてください。
⇒ https://us04web.zoom.us/j/4836797980?pwd=czBocWMvNGZVczlTd0w3WTVNRG9HUT09
アクセスすると、ポップアップと言うのが出てきますので、「アプリケーションを起動」をクリックしてください。

※もし、ポップアップが出て来ない時は、「download & run zoom」と書いてあるところをクリックしてください。
初めてZoomを使用する時は、自動的にアプリがインストールされます。（１－２分かかります）

次回以降は、インストールされているアプリが自動的に起動します。
ミーティングIDとパスワードを入力して下さい。

Zoomが起動すると、画面の中央に「コンピューターでオーディオに参加」という画面が出ますので、緑の部分をクリックしてください。

【スマホの方へ】
アプリを立ち上げて「ミーティングに参加」をタップ。
ミーティングIDとパスワードを入力してください。
iphoneの場合はマイクのアクセスを求められるので「許可」をタップしてください。

Now is a time to connect with others.
We don’t have to be anxious alone.
We can wipe out those feelings with just a little movement :)
That’s what Yoga taught me 👍
Take a deep breath together
Spending time together through the screen.
Beginners and Enthusiast welcome
I am always here with the door of my heart opened:)

■Content
・ 30 minutes class
・ For the first time, let’s introduce each other
・ Practice yoga together through the screen
・for free
・instruction with English and Japanese
・Let’s chat after class

■What you need
・PCs, tablets, and mobile phones with good internet connections. (Laptops and tablets with large screens are recommended.)
・ Yoga mat (can be done on the carpet or flooring if you do not have it, but it is good to have a bath towel so that the knee does not hurt)
*Please RSVP if you can join my class beforehand:)
**To keep our class safe I will give you meeting ID and password via message box individually.

▶︎How to participate

1. RSVP

2. Get a Meeting ID and Password via message box

3. If you use your iphone or tablet, Download Zoom app on your devise beforehand. If you use your laptop you don't need to do that.
I prefer laptop or tablet because easier to see with a big screen.

4. 10 or 15 minute before the class, . Place your yoga mat your comfortable place in your home

5. And then......

【Laptop user】
1. Hit the link down below
This will take you to the Zoom which is the platform with software I am using livestream class
Once you are there you will put meeting ID and password
then click "join"

2. The first time that you do this, you will have to register, so you will have to put your first name, your last name, and email.

3. After click "Register", it will say "open zoom",
in a Mac it will say "allow",
in either case you are just going to click that button, and wait for it to launch should only take a second or two.

4. Click "join with computer audio" and you will see the screen.
It may come up big on your screen, it may not
either way you are probably gonna want full screen
so just click a little square top right corner of the screen

5. click "start video" so I can see you :)
If you dont wanna show yourself in your PJ, click it again

6. Once you are in there, you will see me, you will hear all cues.

7. when our class is over you will just come down to the bottom right and hit "leave meeting"

【iPhone or Tablet user】
Open Zoom app and you will just follow the same sort of cues as above.

events.name: Dewey's 24 Hour Read-a-thon
events.description_html:
Dewey’s 24 Hour Read A Thon ( http://www.24hourreadathon.com/ ) is back!! I love doing this event because I get through a book or two in one day.

On April 25th the Challenge of reading ALL DAY long starts. During the bi-annual read-a-thon we will read books, post to our blogs, Facebook and Twitter or Goodreads about our reading, and visit other readers’ blogs. We will also participate in mini-challenges throughout the day to win prizes. (I love that part!) This event happens twice a year, in April and in October. It was created by a book lover named Dewey. The first one was held in October 2007. Dewey died in late 2008. The read-a-thon was renamed to honor its founder in 2009.

On April 25th the Dewey’s 24 Hour Read-A-Thon ( https://www.24hourreadathon.com/october-2019-reader-sign-up/ ) will start at 5 am for California. If you want to learn more and to sign up, click on the link. There is no money involved and it’s purely for the love of reading on your own pace, for as long or as little as you want.

Go to http://www.24hourreadathon.com/ to learn more and to sign up! Every six hours I will (try to) post a reminder for you to check our book club website with the links to the hourly challenge and Mocha Girls Read challenges. Yes! You can win prizes if you join in.

You don't need to have a blog to participate.

This is an online event and the Dewey website is the host site you check in every couple of hours. This is the best event to get through a few books on your nightstand.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

events.name: [ONLINE] YOU are a BADASS by Jen Sincero - Part 1 of 2 (yellow book)
events.organiser: Messages of Goodness - Pasadena Book Club Meetup
events.description_html:
Hi Messengers,

Are YOU a BADASS?

This is definitely a catchy and funny title, and according to the book's description, "By the end of 'You are a Badass', you'll understand why you are how you are, how to love what you can't change, how to change what you don't love, and how to use The Force to kick some serious ass."

Let's plan to split this over two Meetups.

As members of a BADASS book club (lol), let's dig in and hopefully enjoy some entertainment and lessons along the way!

To comply with our "Safer at Home" order, our Meetup will be conducted ONLINE using Zoom, a free online video conference service. Those that RSVP will receive a link by email, which you can use to quickly and automatically download and install the Zoom software, if you don't already have it. You can then use that same link to connect to our Meetup. I will also post the link to the Meetup site on the morning of the Meetup.

I recommend using a computer or tablet with a microphone, headphones, and speaker; however, it's possible to use your phone as long as you are in a quiet place. If you have a camera, I recommend enabling video, which will help make the connection more personal.

Until our next Meetup, please continue spreading, reading, or listening to Messages of Goodness!

To avoid spending a lot of money, please check out the following options:

1. Purchase an inexpensive, used version, generally found online
2. Check out an audible or hard copy from your local library
3. Scan YouTube for summaries
4. Check the OverDrive app, which works with your local libraries for audible/ebooks.

Hope to meet or see you soon!
Frances

we're going to do this online. we'll try Google Hangouts. (thanx Camilla!) as soon as i figure out how to do that, i'll post it on here. OR google hangouts. we'll see!

Where the Crawdads Sing by Delia Owens

This book has been on my To-Read list for almost a year. It is time to finally get to it! The reviews for it are interesting. the people that like it absolutely love it. 61% of its readers gave it 5 stars! that's a pretty good chunk. we tend to be pretty selfish with our stars, in this book club, so i'm excited to see how we will feel about it. the people that wrote bad reviews on it are absolute in their disdain for what has become such a popular book. will any of those people be among us in april? hmmm...

i am hoping that late april will be enough time to get through the fear that the corona-virus has brought. I hope you are all staying healthy!

happy reading!

events.name: When We Were Orphans by Kazuo Ishiguro - POSTPONED
events.description_html: Born in early-twentieth-century Shanghai, Banks was orphaned at the age of nine after the separate disappearances of his parents. Now, more than twenty years later, he is a celebrated figure in London society; yet the investigative expertise that has garnered him fame has done little to illuminate the circumstances of his parents' alleged kidnappings. Banks travels to the seething, labyrinthine city of his memory in hopes of solving the mystery of his own, painful past, only to find that war is ravaging Shanghai beyond recognition-and that his own recollections are proving as difficult to trust as the people.

events.name: Longmont Book Club - The Keeper of Lost Things by Ruth Hogan
events.description_html:
I will host this event on the GoToMeeting platform and will send out details soon. Please sign up if you are interested in attending. -Gerty

Anthony Peardew is the keeper of lost things. Forty years ago, he carelessly lost a keepsake from his beloved fiancée, Therese. That very same day, she died unexpectedly. Brokenhearted, Anthony sought consolation in rescuing lost objects—the things others have dropped, misplaced, or accidentally left behind—and writing stories about them. Now, in the twilight of his life, Anthony worries that he has not fully discharged his duty to reconcile all the lost things with their owners. As the end nears, he bequeaths his secret life’s mission to his unsuspecting assistant, Laura, leaving her his house and and all its lost treasures, including an irritable ghost.

Recovering from a bad divorce, Laura, in some ways, is one of Anthony’s lost things. But when the lonely woman moves into his mansion, her life begins to change. She finds a new friend in the neighbor’s quirky daughter, Sunshine, and a welcome distraction in Freddy, the rugged gardener. As the dark cloud engulfing her lifts, Laura, accompanied by her new companions, sets out to realize Anthony’s last wish: reuniting his cherished lost objects with their owners.

Long ago, Eunice found a trinket on the London pavement and kept it through the years. Now, with her own end drawing near, she has lost something precious—a tragic twist of fate that forces her to break a promise she once made.

As the Keeper of Lost Objects, Laura holds the key to Anthony and Eunice’s redemption. But can she unlock the past and make the connections that will lay their spirits to rest?

events.name: Virtual Book Club: the sun and her flowers
events.description_html:
**PLEASE NOTE: This will be a virtual meetup via Zoom.**
Meeting ID:[masked]
Password:[masked]

Let's celebrate National Poetry Month with a special *second* book club meeting this month where we'll discuss Rupi Kaur's other collection of poetry, "The Sun and Her Flowers."

"From Rupi Kaur, the #1 New York Times bestselling author of milk and honey, comes her long-awaited second collection of poetry. A vibrant and transcendent journey about growth and healing. Ancestry and honoring one’s roots. Expatriation and rising up to find a home within yourself.

Divided into five chapters and illustrated by Kaur, the sun and her flowers is a journey of wilting, falling, rooting, rising, and blooming. A celebration of love in all its forms.

this is the recipe of life
said my mother
as she held me in her arms as i wept
think of those flowers you plant
in the garden each year
they will teach you
that people too
must wilt
fall
root
rise
in order to bloom"

Synopsis from Goodreads.com.

events.name: Virtual Queer Sewing Circle
events.description_html:
While we're all stuck at home with nothing to do, I'm planning to just make sewing circle a weekly Saturday morning thing. Join for crafts, talking about feelings, and bonding. There's no requirement to do crafts, I just wanted to have a standing time for queer community. I'll be online for about 4 hours, so jump in whenever! Link will be posted later!

Let's do some crafts together ON THE INTERNET! This is not limited to just sewing, I just want to call it a sewing circle. Do whatever craft you want! We've had people sew, knit, crochet, work on things on their computers, color, or just hang out and chat. Do whatever project you're working on or none at all!xt

Unfortunately I won't be able to share supplies because we'll be remote but even if you're just there to chat and hangout, that's great! Just getting to spend time together while we're all stuck inside is awesome.

events.name: Opera on Sydney Harbour - La Traviata
events.summary: Doors open 2 hours prior to performance time. Raise your glass, flutter those lashes. He's staring at you, he's singing for you… Are you tempted? Violetta is the life of every party. A courtesan with a heart of gold, she's free and free-spirited. Could a little love change everything? Experience the joy and heartache of the world's most popular opera at Sydney's best night out. Fireworks light up the sky at every performance. A giant chandelier shimmers over the harbour stage. Handa Opera on Sydney Harbour is "the ultimate Sydney experience" (Yahoo! Travel). Arrive early to enjoy drinks or dinner at one of the five pop-up bars and restaurants on site. Drink in the view as the setting sun glimmers over the city skyline. Then take your seats in the comfortable grandstand to enjoy "a ravishing visual spectacle" (Huffington Post). Brian Castles-Onion conducts the opera, with a live orchestra hidden under the stage.

Please note: The stunts performed in Nitro Circus Live are amongst the most dangerous in the world. When athletes are attempting insane stunts 40 feet in the air over a 75 foot gap, the weather conditions have to be perfect as the onset of rain, dew, wind or other factors could be fatal. That's why we are reserving one or more additional days (Sunday 28th February or Monday 1st March 2021 ) as possible alternative show dates in case we need to reschedule. When you buy your ticket, please make sure that you are available on the reserve days too in case we have to use them for a rescheduled show. If we do, there are no refunds.

events.name: Newcastle Knights v Penrith Panthers
events.summary: The 2020 NRL season will be impacted by the Government's directive that we suspend attendance by the general public at matches in Round 2 and until further notice. The NRL is working closely with clubs, states and the game's partners to address issues associated with the closure of matches to members and fans of the game (and other scenarios that may present). NRL Telstra Premiership games will be temporarily held from sale until further notice. We will provide our valued members and fans with updates as information about our approach comes to hand via NRL, club and state channels. Now, as much as ever, we value your constant support and understanding. Rugby league is known for its resilience and we know we will work through this together.

events.name: NSW Waratahs v Rebels
events.summary: Sydney's northern beaches turned it on in 2019, packing the hills of Brookvale Oval to support their Tahs and we want to fill 'Brookie' again this season! The second of three consecutive derbies at home, we'll take on a Melbourne Rebels side featuring the likes of Isi Naisarani, Marika Koroibete and Reece Hodge. Come and enjoy Super Rugby in the suburbs as we look to continue our winning ways against the Rebels! Run Times: 4:30pm - Gates open 7:15pm - Kick-off 9:00pm - Finish (approx.) *Please note times are approximate and subject to change. Concession applies Full-time Students, Pensioners and Seniors with valid ID. A Family Ticket consists of 2 Adults and 2 Juniors 4-16 Years.

events.name: GWS GIANTS v Collingwood
events.summary: Junior Policy: Junior tickets are for Juniors 6-14 years. Juniors 5 years & under are admitted free providing they do not occupy a seat. For children under 2 years, please contact the GIANTS on (02) 8736 4200 Persons 15 years & over as at 1-Jan-20 are classified as an adult. Family Tickets: Family tickets are Comprised of 2 Adults & 2 Juniors 6-14 years. Concession Policy: Concession tickets are available for holders of: - Pensioner Concession Card - DVA card or DVA issued Pensioner Concession Card - Full Time Australian secondary/tertiary student cards (not international students) - Health Care Card

events.name: GWS GIANTS v Collingwood - Premium Experience
events.summary: The St.George Skydeck Premium Experience includes: - General Admission seating in the Skydeck (Level 4) - Gourmet BBQ buffet - Cash bar (tab option available) with premium beverages, including spirits, available to purchase - Post-match bar service The First Class Premium Experience includes: - Premium Reserve seat located in the Vincent Fairfax stand (Level 3) - In-seat valet service for all your food & beverage needs - A complimentary Food and Beverage voucher Junior Policy: Juniors 5-15 Years. Juniors under 5 years are admitted free of charge into the ground providing they do not occupy a seat. For children under 2 years, please contact the GIANTS on (02) 8736 4200
